{"text": "I cannot think of an FPS I've ever enjoyed more than this one. (I haven't played the sequel yet though!) A fantastic shooter that brings a second meaning to the term FPS: First Person Swordplay. Sword skills vary between offensive and defensive and make you feel very powerful. The choice is yours though: you can almost exclusively use either guns or melee combat, as long as you're sane enough not to ramp the difficulty all the way up. Upgrade system adds a rewarding element of progression and unlocking. The levels are quite long and varied for an FPS and some of the scenery is like eye candy to me. As a fan of the original, I feel Flying Wild Hog have done a good job retaining the spirit the game's forebearer and included plenty of funny one-liners that work well. A brutal but envigorating challenge on the highest difficulty (make sure you choose the right skills early on...). It's going to be a long slug taking down bosses and mini-bosses if you go down this road :) So good I bought it on 2 platforms. Update: still highly recommend this game in 2017. The sequel is quite different and I miss certain aspects of this one.", "appid": "233130", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970366868", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1381406400.0}
