{"text": "Fallout 4 has vey good graphics, compared to the other Fallout and Bethesda games. This is a very good game with a lot of choices to take. You can choose from four different factions with a brilliant main story line. Sadly I don't have any DLC on PC but I have on PS4. It's worth buying season pass for this instead of wasting money by buying the seperatly. Some may say that only Nuka World and Far Harbor are the only DLCs worth getting... well, if you buy the season pass you will save more of your money in the length, while at the same time getting more for it. The V.A.T.S and ranking up system is very balanced aswell like the previos Fallout games, and the V.A.T.S can be usefull for every combat situation. Final rating from me would be 9,2/10 since the price is maybe a bit too high. If you are wealthy this will not be a problem. Other than that a very good game with a good story line and you can easily spend many hours into this game.", "appid": "377160", "steamid": "profiles/76561198286475481", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1480334400.0}
