{"text": "Voodoo Vince is a bit of a period piece: The voice acting and basic plot remind me of the Saturday morning cartoons of the 80's and 90's. If you don't mind a little campiness (and I don't at all) this games storyline will bring you back to simpler times. That said where a game like this makes it or breaks it is on the strength of it's platforming and puzzling. Fortunately Voodoo Vince succeeds at both. While the camera is not 100% perfect, it's not bad and the controls feel spot-on -- not a common thing in platformers from the early 2000's.  Graphics are nice and crisp and I like the soundtrack quite a bit. If you have a low end PC there are settings to scale things down a bit and obviously any gaming PC will run it nicely. If you missed this game on the original XBox or just want to re-live good times Voodoo Vince is well woth putting some time into. GPD Win based review/ let's play linked:", "appid": "545980", "steamid": "profiles/76561197986325765", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1492862400.0}
