{"text": "While many would describe Hitman: Absoultion as the \"black sheep\" of the series, I enjoyed the time I spent with it thoroughly. I agree that stripping away alot of the Stealth and Sandbox Aspects of the franchise were a step in the wrong direction, but still a curageous step that hadn't been taken before - what I mean by that is, that with the more action-based approach you get to see a side of Hitman Games you wouldn't normally get to explore in the older/newer entries and that is very much to be respected. Also Absolution has an amazing Soundtrack in my opinion, of course that's a feature of the entire franchise itself, but the suspense carried by the music here is something not many, even action-oriented games, match. As for the story I also like the more personal approach to Agent 47 as a protagonist here, you learn alot about him and have him interact with the world and others way more often and in depth then he does in the other games where he is strictly bound by his current contract and Diana's guidance. Furthermore our \"villains\" in this story are very fleshed out, well voiced and feel more like Antagonists that you want to track down and take revenge on, a feat that the previous games didn't accomplish that well, with previous villains being pretty forgettable in my opinion.", "appid": "203140", "steamid": "profiles/76561198091317533", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1599825600.0}
