{"text": "Okay, to be honest, the game is good, a real classic in the SRPG genre. I'm giving a soft recomendation to this game and here's my reasons (and no, I'm not mad that they didn't include the full OST in the digital soundtrack, I can understand NISA for not being able to secure the rights of that on the due time due to unforeseen events): - Issues with the game performance (I didn't have issues with the graphics, only slowdown on heavy animations like the Geo Chain Explosion, Hurricane Slash, Adonic Blast, and maybe so many others) --Fixed most of the performance bits on the March 2 update, but I've heard that CoO3 has been broken. - A rehash of the PSP version, which means, no playable Pleinair (I got the Mid-boss Ending to corroborate this, and it didn't unlock the playable version of this character), and I think that means there's no playable versions of the extra bosses in the new area that's included in the PSP version. Also, the lack of the features from the DS version, maybe it's due to licensing issues, but wouldn't be possible to program those features here? - This is a personal one, but the lack of options to help speeding up the game even more like in the DS version (I know that in the PSP version it was included the option to skip battle animations), as in including the option for speeding up the Geo Chain animations and walking animations in battle (IIRC), or even better (this hasn't been on any version of the game AFAIK) skipping the story cutscenes, etc... I know, I know, based on the PSP version, but wasn't even possible to add these to begin with for this version? Surely this sounds like a pet peeve, I'm just expressing my opinion here. I know I'm rambing too long for being a rehash of the PSP version, but those are just nitpicks. Seeing how NISA has been updating this game, I have faith in seeing more added content on the future. tl;dr I recommend this game, but it's a soft recommendation. If they can iron out all the issues, maybe it will get a full recommendation from me, but who knows?", "appid": "405900", "steamid": "profiles/76561198208604827", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1456315200.0}
{"text": "8/12/19 HALO Reach part: Classical feelings with a classic game. Game has still to get optimized, definitely. At some times I have FPS drops or screen freezing. Sound is also sometimes after the action. Controlling feels really good and smooth, you can set your hotkey also by your own. Playing this game with controller is also no bad choice because of slightly auto-aim. Sounds are like in the past game. Graphics are like in the past game (but you can set them slightly higher, but it may cause more FPS drops, even when your PC is more then enough for the specs). In this HALO Reach version you've got everything HALO offered, so enjoy it. I really have my good old times back, I am just so happy about it - thanks 343 for not giving up HALO! All in all: Graphics: Same Sounds: Same Controlling: 10/10 Includings: 10/10 Performance: 7/10", "appid": "976730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198087322896", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "12", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1575720000.0}
