{"text": "I bought Hell Let Loose on its release day (D-Day). I absolutely Love Hell Let Loose. This game is like the middle child of Red Orchestra 2 and Post Scriptum. Not too arcade oriented, not too tactical or realistic. It's like a fine Garlic Bread. Of course the game could be better. This is a beta review after all. I would like to see the addition of opening the hatches on tanks to look out and possibly the addition a machine gun on the turret for the commander ( available while out of the hatch). It would be nice to allow infantry to ride on tanks too. As of now it feels like a running and tanking simulator. The addition of day and nigh cycles plus weather affects would be very nice and add immersion. The Graphics are amazing and the game play is fun. Needs improvements but its still fun at this current stage, I really enjoy Hell Let Loose, I give it a 7/10. Keep up the good work devs, you really have something special here.", "appid": "686810", "steamid": "profiles/76561198144561483", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "62", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1560168000.0}
