{"text": "The   franchise has always been a love letter to gaming in a way, with each title emulating a different set of genres, subgenres and games (which also compliments the idea that each Horseman is unique).   continues that tradition and takes parts of its inspiration from the   and   subgenres, in addition to everything else, offering the most punishing and methodical combat so far and an elemental-/ weapon-upgrade-based progression. The game offers two different Combat Modes, \"Default\" and \"Classic\", as well as five difficulty settings, that you can choose from when you start a new game. \"Classic\" mode is more similar to the first two games and more forgiving by allowing you to cancel your attacks with a dodge and skipping the animation when using an item. By combining the two modes with the five difficulty settings there is a lot of freedom for players and the game can be fairly easy as well as frustratingly difficult. For those that want to experience the plot and lore first and foremost, Classic + Story/Balanced would probably be ideal, while fans of the   subgenre might prefer Default + Apocalyptic. Since the game also offers the so-called \"Armageddon\" Mode (NG+), it makes sense to start out easier and save the harder experience for subsequent playthroughs. The game is set after the prologue of the first   and before the rest of it, 100 years later, much like the second game. It is set before   and sees the player tasked with recapturing the  , that have escaped their prison when the Apocalypse happened and have now made Earth their domain.   starts out extremely uncharismatic and uncaring but has a big character arc over the course of the game, with many events prompting her to reconsider her stance on certain topics. The voice acting got mixed reactions but I think the voice actors all work really well with what they're given. Due to   constant anger and early disregard of others, her performance probably feels the weakest but even she works well in the context of the story. The cutscenes are all very well made but I saw the \"plot-twist\" coming very early on. The graphics of the game are fine, nothing mind-blowing but definitely not bad. What really makes it shine is the art-style and the way it portrays the post-Apocalypse Earth. Cris Velasco, the composer of the first game's soundtrack, returns and delivers a score that is just as epic and also manages to be varied and have some very memorable tracks. It's not quite on the level of Jesper Kyd's work for the second game but it's great nonetheless. While the game was very rough at launch, and still is on consoles, it now runs really well and only really rarely and briefly has the random loading that you may know from video reviews. Some containers lack a texture for some reason but other than that, I encountered no issues. Tested with the following setup:  has received very mixed feedback but quite frankly, it's a good game and a good continuation of the series. It does have its flaws, as we explored in this review, but it managed to captivate me for countless hours on several systems. I definitely recommend this as long as you know what to expect.", "appid": "606280", "steamid": "profiles/76561198008869914", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "111", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1593864000.0}
{"text": "Childhood reborn ;-; Harvest Moon Back to Nature (Story of Seasons now) is easily the best \"farming sim\" experience i had and this game just makes it all the better It's like the original GBA version + BTN All the characters and musics are here, even though the portraits are kind of different they are still pretty good IMO everything is so cute :> I cannot recommend this game enough, if you are interested in farming sims or you are an OG Harvest Moon fan you should definitely buy it! Story: of seasons/10 Gameplay: 10/10(great mechanics as always) Music: 9/10(I prefer some of the original OSTs, but they are still pretty good) Graphics: 10/10(great visuals + the animations are very well done, also thank you Marvelous and XSEED for another MARVELOUS port XD) P.S: I'd say you should tinker with AA options on Nvidia control panel if you're not running 4K for best experience HAPPY FARMING \\o/", "appid": "978780", "steamid": "profiles/76561198044477182", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "20", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594728000.0}
