{"text": "This is a great sequel to the original hotline miami which was also a great game.  If you have played the original hotline miami, the gameplay of this one is much like the original but focused on multiple characters rather than just one. For those who haven't played hotline maimi, it is an unforgiving strategy game in which one hit will kill you and spawns you at the beginning of whatever floor you were on. It is not impossible and nothing about this game is impossible. However it is very challenging and might not be for everybody. But what i can reccomend to everybody is the soundtrack. I'm pretty sure everybody can agree the soundtrack is probably one of the best parts of the game and it fits very well in with the aesthetic of the game, which is a retro themed game based around miami in the 80's. If I were to give this game a rating and a crowd reccomendation it would have to be a 10/10 and mainly for the audience that enjoys simplicity yet challenge.", "appid": "274170", "steamid": "profiles/76561198079338113", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1468065600.0}
{"text": "it's not fortnite", "appid": "440", "steamid": "profiles/76561198072525258", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1562241600.0}
{"text": "This game is awesome, who doesn't want to break a door down and blow a terrorist head off? I've played the game for a couple hours so far, it fun and very interesting, however, remember that this is still an alpha, so not even a beta yet, so don't expect everything to be polished or the game to be at its full. The game can be pretty frustrating at times, for example I don't understand the use of stealth weapons, it doesn't change anything, enemies hear you and come to investigate. I hate this, i like playing stealthy by as soon as one shot from a stealth weapon  goes off, enemies come to see what the noise was then â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ turns into cluster â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ central. I do hope they actually fix this, if they did then this game would definitely be on my top 5 game list.  There's this a lot missing from the game, for example not all of the upgrades are available, there's no campaign so you just go through different stages and shoot at people. One of the most frustrating missions are hostage rescue missions, at first they are nice and all but after a couple stages, they start executing hostages, so if you break a door or shoot at someone, you have 5 seconds to reach the hostages before they are executed,  which isn't easy in a big house/office... Also, it seems SWAT doesn't care much for hostages, if they see an enemy and there's a hostage in-between them, they just shoot at them and kill the hostage, which is especially annoying since if you kill a hostage, or a hostage dies, it's mission failed. Don't expect it to be a Call of Duty like game where one person takes on an entire building full of terrorists, you will almost always be out-numbered so you have to plan ahead of time, and be ready to adapt when things don't go your way.  I would recommend this game if you like games like XCOM but remember, this is still an alpha and there's a lot missing.", "appid": "248610", "steamid": "profiles/76561198038318187", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1400846400.0}
