{"text": "I had fun with it. I was playing on my friend's account before i decided to buy it on 90% ( since i'm poor af lmao ) Pros : + Interesting & playable gameplay ( not as buggy as other ubisoft's games ) + Fun multiplayer ( like having players invading your world and â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ on you from afar? i always dream of this ) + Combat & stealth is somewhat between fine and good ( It's something you'd expect from a stealth gunnin' game ) + Blackout ( dope â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ ) Somewhat between pros and cons: * Has kinda interesting story mode... has plot holes though. Cons : - E3 downgrade - Had problems when starting the game on the Steam version and had to find workarounds.  - No customization. You literally can only pick colors & styles of your coat & hat, nothing else. Can't flex your cars with your own colors too. - Doesn't have that much parkour since there aren't many buildings you can climb on, because you cannot get a helicopter. Modes : Multiplayer : Consists of 5 modes : Decryption ( basically it is Capture & Hold the flag but with technologies and stuffs instead of a physical flag ), 1v1 Hacking / Tailing ( invade people's world when they are on single player mode to â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ on them. You do have the ability to stop others coming in btw ), Free roam ( basically GTA V's online mode but laggier and less aggressive ) and Racing. Single player : Consists of 2 story mode ( if bought T-Bone's DLC ), many side stories, gang place wiping, racing, pokers, withstand the drinks, criminal busting. My score : 8 / 10 . I wish someday they'd come back to this game and polish it a bit more... I kinda prefer this over GTA V's multiplayer, for some reason.", "appid": "243470", "steamid": "profiles/76561198261032304", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1559304000.0}
