{"text": "Read this VN to kill some time. Got an interesting character study and story. Took me 1.6 hours and I consider it time decently well spent. It's also free! The story follows Lynne, a teen who is in a stressful family situation. Her older sister is unemployed and pregnant, and the family lives in an old, cramped house (Lynne shares a bunk bed with her pregnant sister and has never had her own room). As time passes, the story explores the pressures and expectations of Lynne from her father, and the apathy towards her by the people around her. Lynne starts to crack and her mental state deteriorates throughout the story. I personally found the story interesting as a character study - the world isn't particularly deep but just being taken for the ride in someone else's mind is something that I read VNs for, and I got it with Lynne. Recommend if you're feeling something moody / grim and have 1.5 hours or so to spare.", "appid": "885640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198069420601", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1564833600.0}
