{"text": "I normally do not review games very seriously, but I feel this is an exception. In the start this game is really hard to learn and there is a lot to take in, but from the little I've played I have begun to pick up the basic skills of crafting, and refilling tools. The story is not the best one out there, alot of it gets repetitive and you just need to travel down to different planets in order to craft new stuff. If you are in to exploration, then there is no better game than this. No Man's Sky has the biggest map out of all video games (i think). For me personally it gets repetitive and I can't sit down and play the game for 8 hours straight without it getting boring. The main part I decided to review this game is the mechanics and enviorment! This is why I really love this game, you will definitely discover a brand new planet which no one else has been on in your career of No Man's Sky, and that planet will be completely unique to any others! Every planet has it's own eco-system and enviorment, some planets are highly toxic and others rain fire. You really never know what to expect when arriving on a new planet. Scavanging resources is kinda exciting. Not all planets has what you're looking for, you might need to travel a big distance to get what you are looking for, luckily they have a feature to scan planets for their resources so you don't have to visit every single planet to find out if they contain what you are looking for. I would rate this game a solid 8/10 just based of the mechanics and randomness..", "appid": "275850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198096562599", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1547467200.0}
