{"text": "I have got to say, this has hit the scales as one of my favorite space games that is not a massive multiplayer scale. I had originally gotten Starpoint Gemini 2 on one of its free spells. After a fair bit of playing, I took some looking into this game and am beyond thrilled with it. The playstyle starts off slow and picks up very fast. All in all, for what this game is, it succeeds by leaps and bounds. Wish that it shared the same framerate as SPG2, but that relates to personal specs only. All in all, I'd rate this game a solid 9.2 out of 10. Graphics are fantastic, audio is gorgeous. Story content is very enjoyable, replayability is through the roof due to how many takes you can get on the system at large. The addition of an RTS style for faction management makes this a must have for those who want an enjoyable, customizeable space experience without relying on multiplayer. The modding support is also superb, even non-modders can figure out an easy way of changing a few things to add in custom features. So this game really is what you want it to be. Happy Warmongering.", "appid": "419480", "steamid": "profiles/76561198021621725", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1548936000.0}
