{"text": "Party hard 2 is a game about a guy getting waken up by his neighbors at 3 am so he decides to go on a killing spree to make things tranquil. The game is a combination between Hitman and Hotline Miami. The graphics are stunning and the gameplay is comforting and challenging. Party hard 2 is the perfect sequel to party hard with upgraded animations, better voice acting but still preferably bad but the sounds are excellent though. If you're familiar with the prequel then you know how the game works. You enter a party with a dozen other people. The goal varies from missions. but most of the times the goal is to kill everyone or some specific targets, drug dealers etc. To accomplish your goal you get to use your trusty knife and the environment for an example. sabotage the speakers to explode, poison the drinks or throw people into a fire. But you need to be careful not to get caught murdering because the witness will then call the police and it isn't fun hiding from them. This game makes party hard 1 look like game jam game in my opinion. As i stated earlier, every game of Party hard starts with you outside a huge party, the levels vary from MC gatherings to hospitals parties. But the goal is usually the same, to kill everyone or specific targets. Some levels may also have some level themed quests for an example explode 5 trucks. A new feature that is important to mention is the new abilities. Every character has unique abilities for an example the \"party hard killers\" ability is to cause a shockwave abolishing everyone in the surrounding. Crafting is also a new important feature that gives you the ability to combine items and create new bizarre items that can be used to exterminate a good example is when you combine a lighter and a full gas can you will create a bomb that can be used to kill a large number of crowded people. Party hard 2 is currently out for 16,79â‚¬ which i think is fairly priced. It's about 4â‚¬ more than the prequel but you get a more enhanced experience. 13 unique missions that take about 30-45 minutes each to complete if you are experienced with the party hard series. There is also a decent amount of replayability because there are multiple quests on every level and a lot of different ways to murder people.   The game is mostly balanced but there's one thing i hoped they could have improved in the sequel that i hated in party hard 1. And it's the fact that the police instantly knows where you are when a person calls them. It just doesn't make sense that the police instantly starts to chase you after them being called. And i believe they could have implemented another mechanic, for an example alternatively of having 1-2 cops that know where you are. they should make maybe 5-8 cops that seek for you or something like that, so they'll nerf the cops but still keep the game somewhat challenging. This game is insanely difficult for newcomers and casual gamers. Because it isn't easy killing people with a bunch of people nearby. Because as fast as they witness you committing murder the police will arrive and the odds of you succeeding to evade them is very low. I usually make a kind of plan on who i am going to take out in what order and then just wait out people to go into deserted rooms. The graphics are stunning. The textures are a lot less pixelated since the prequel and level design is now 3D with 2D Characters. The use of small detailed pixels like fire particles really enhances the experience a lot. The animations are very smooth, and the use of shadows makes the atmosphere feel alive. The soundtrack of Party hard 2 is really catchy and gets easily stuck in my head. And really much all sounds from the sirens of the cops to the sounds of murdering with the knife is really high quality. And a huge improvement from the prequel. Runs really well on my setup with post 60fps. Was a bit of a surprise because i thought it would be at the sub 60's because of all the entities loaded into the game and all of the activity going on. -Police is a bit too overpowered -When taking shortcuts i sometimes end up getting stuck in the ground and unable to move. But it has only happened twice during my 10-hour playthrough and I use shortcuts a lot. Most of the bugs are also patched at this date so you'll most likely not experience my issues when playing.  Party hard 2 is the excellent sequel to its predecessor party hard. The graphics are stunning and a lot of new interesting features that no one expected. The game is perfect with a few flaws such as the police is a bit broken and small bugs that may sometimes be a bit annoying.", "appid": "572430", "steamid": "profiles/76561198140378650", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1542024000.0}
