{"text": "Well it truly is a Game of Thrones experience. While it definately lacks the diversity in storyline outcomes that a typical good rpg ussually offers, it makes up for it with a powerful dose of immersion. You'll find yourself in the shoes of lesser yet still immerssive characters right out of the books and show that have become so iconic and well loved. Laughter will be had, choices will be reloaded and redone (many times), much sorrow will be had, and plenty of death along the way. There is no happy ending story here so if you were expecting a fairy tale look elsewhere.  This is as close to the show/books as you can ever get to immersing yourself in Westeros. Best of luck in your adventures & remember these two things: - Iron From Ice - The North Remembers", "appid": "330840", "steamid": "profiles/76561198060388644", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1448971200.0}
