{"text": "This is definitely a much better step up compared to Rome II. I really enjoyed the Romance mode aspect as it definitely follows the same trait as Warhammer 2 mechanic in regards to heroes but with this mode it has a much stronger presence making battles especially with duels epic and interesting to see how it plays out while your troops battle in the background. However there are occasionally a few bugs here and there and some visual glitches but the most frustrating is the AI somehow getting an advantage at times where it shouldn't be  able to. The biggest culprit is the autoresolve where I had a few rare occasions where I had an army unstoppable get destroyed by a weaker force due to the wonky balance in the auto resolve so I tend to manually fight my battles even if a good amount are just a waste of time when my time and effort can be put to better use in my empire. There is of course the DLC but its expected for them to do this, pretty sure they are no better than Paradox Interactive but sadly not much to be done in regards to that. Overall would recommend this game to anyone not familiar with the Total War series and of course veterans.", "appid": "779340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198062204311", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "12", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1575201600.0}
