{"text": "The best F2P game I've played so far.  At first I saw just a standard FPS game where you just ran and shoot. But after progress a little further I found out there's more to this game than just a standard FPS. You'll see there's lots of things to do, and what makes this game rather unique is that you can equip any Warframe(s) and Weapons you prefer the most. Be aware that certain Warframes won't be good for certain type of missions since Warframes have their strenght and weakness. What I also liked about this game is that the further you go, more things will be unlocked and you'll be rewarded with   (if you want to unlock without knowing before hand, don't read the spoiler). One thing I must mentioned before you start playing this (this I can \"spoil\") is... in order to make your Warframe, weapons, etc. stronger is that you will need to equip mods. And in case you don't have a clue what's that mod good for, I would recommend you to do loads of research anywhere (steam, google, yt, etc.) and also play in co op with your friend or friends, otherwise you might be stuck in some planets since mods are the essential to make a Warframe OP (you'll be able to upgrade those mods.  Before I forget, there's journeys in the game that I recommend playing so you can know more about the lore of the Warframe and also unlock the rewards I mention in the spoiled text. One thing that I can also point out (this one a bit negatively) is that some planets have the same level design (you'll know which is which when you play and unlock), although that doesn't prevent you having fun playing it. With that said, I would recommend you give it a try and when the game \"clicks\" (if \"clicks\"), you'll have loads of fun. P.S - I almost forgot to mention this... what also makes this game worth playing is that everything can be farmed, (even the rarest itens) and that will require farming it (some of those things will require loads of time farming it, and believe me, it will take loads of time indeed). In case you don't have that much patient, you can buy it with your platinum.", "appid": "230410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198158982433", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1562414400.0}
