{"text": "On the first look, Undertale looks just like any other Indie game and you would assume that it's nothing special. Well, thats not the case at all. Undertale, which is heavily influenced by the 1994 released game \"EarthBound\" takes you on a beautiful journey full of genius, scary and funny characters, who have their own little story to tell. I don't want to spoil the story at this point, but there are three different ways to play the story. Normal, which is when you kill some characters and spare others; Pacifist, which is when you spare everyone; and genocide, which is when you kill everyone. And at this point I just want to list the pro's and con's of this game, since I think that Undertale is most enjoyable when you don't know as much as possible. Pro's: -Great soundtrack, hands down. Even for a game with a high budget this would have been impressive, but as an indie game which was made by a very small team, this is just unbelievable -Awesome characters which you learn to love while the story continues -Great story with a choosable ending -Can you count nostalgic 8 bit graphics as a pro? -The difficulty isn't hard, but it's also not the easiest in the world. I think it's fair and it's a good gateway to such games to new players -Humorous -The game is made for an audience of every age -The feeling of the different locations are astounding Con's: -The game itself is a little short -I would have loved to see a multiplayer, but sadly this is a singleplayer only game But even the Con's are completely understandable when you consider that this game was made by just a few people. Long story short: It's an awesome game. If you can afford $10 on a short but loveable indie game, then I would recommend you to go for it. 9.5/10", "appid": "391540", "steamid": "profiles/76561198161157355", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1543924800.0}
