{"text": "The much-lauded Titanfall 2...  I've heard so much about this game, and I've watched friends play it and I must say it does look and play incredibly. The sheer speed an intensity of the game is a twitch shooter unlike any I've ever played. It takes the pulse-pounding arena shooter experience of old and dials it up to 11. Then ontop of that you call in giant robots to trash each other! As of writing this review I've only dipped a toe into the campaign and played some half dozen MP matches but I'm having a blast. Many are put off MP because of those big, mean, experienced MP players but honestly, I clued myself up on respawn's own \"beginner's guide to multiplayer\" and the rest is just experience. If you're pedestrian, you'll get shot. If you march your titan down the middle of the map with no backup, it'll get blown up. Play smart. Play the objective. You'll learn the maps as you go. Soon the multikills will come rolling in when you're speeding around dropping fools like a maniac, or simply because you're holding a good angle with Scorch and everyone keeps walking into your flame traps. If you're looking for an arcade-style shooter that rewards keen reflexes, good decision making, BIG ROBOTS WITH CHAINGUNS, and something that's not your typical \"team shooter\" then I highly recommend giving this a try.", "appid": "1237970", "steamid": "profiles/76561197960901532", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1595678400.0}
