{"text": "I really like this game, it has some flaws, and some bugs but nothing gamebreaking, people are complaining about the reload mechanics of the game but i am playing on hardest difficulty and doesn't have any problem with it, i guess people except that all the games will be like call of duty, \"Killing one enemy and reloading after it\", but this game is totally inspired by the old resident evils. For being the first game of the devs i think they did a really good work, the game has lots of references of the 90's and you can clearly see that they put some effort in the details. Definitely worth the purchase in a sale, mostly if you like survivor horror games with inventory management and where every bullet count.", "appid": "842100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198037085103", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1589112000.0}
