{"text": "Do keep in mind, this is an early access game and still under development with more content being added. So for god's sake, give the developer some constructive feedback on what can be improved so they can work on it! I'm literally surprised with all the hate & whining about the game lacks content, bug issues & so on. Sure it does have flaw like crashes while in-game, I had few during the first hour after launching the game, but you have the option to revert back to DX11 instead of Vulcan, as the developer suggest. It works actually. I both love and hate this game but for all good reason, sure it has performance issue while in-game but honestly it's not even the final version at the moment. So, if this is not what you want to experience first hand, you should probably wait until it is fully done. This EA gave the hindsight on the realms in BG3, the characters you meet starts with an epic prologue and what's intrigues me is the storyline and the curiosity that it builds further in the game. How you interact with characters in the game changes everything and the relationship with others around you. Everyone has their own edgy attitudes..lol.  For the gameplay, you have all the possibilities to attack your foes, you can literally throw anything on your foes, even junks you loot from the corpses! boots, hats, foods..you name it! The soundtracks really bring the mood while in-game during combat and off-combat, and it has darn good voice acting for the characters in game, each NPC have unique voice. BG3 is a turn based CRPG using 5e ruleset so if you are familiar with this type of game you will like it!", "appid": "1086940", "steamid": "profiles/76561199060197746", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1605182400.0}
