{"text": "Short and sweet game which I would highly recommend with multiple choices on what you want to do and path to follow (I'm going to be vague to insure I don't spoil anything story wise), it has everything from jumping around a building to running through the doors of said building knocking out whom every dares get in the way. It won't take you long to finish the game (I did it on my first try of the game in one sitting) which can be seen as either good or bad, BUT the game is done so well that it makes you want to play again, and see how you could do things differently. Finally, at the end of it all you get to 'write' (as in using pre written sentences) a personilised 'blog' about how your character felt about the game and stats such as the amount of money earnt and people you 'legally' accidently kiiindaa killed just because you got a bit carried away while punching them or like making them fall through windows. P.S. I would recommend getting the special edition for the soundtrack, it's really good and sets the atmosphere for the game. Here's my characters 'blog' at the end of my first game-", "appid": "206190", "steamid": "profiles/76561198057813639", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1434542400.0}
