{"text": "This isn't so much of a game as it is a sweet, wistful experience of reliving a childhood memory of a Japanese boy spending time at home on a cozy rainy day. You get to explore your snug little house, engage in nice and mellow conversations with your family, and discover some cute items associated with pleasant memories and daydreams while indulging in a chill, calming ambience. Essentially, it's a very short and simple story with an emphasis on the atmosphere which is incredibly peaceful and brought me a feeling of comfort, warmth, and relaxation with a touch of melancholy and a sense of nostalgia, taking me back to the good old times of looking at the world through the eyes of a carefree child. The only downside for me was clunky interaction/controls, but nothing to spoil my overall impression of this lovely game.", "appid": "1094420", "steamid": "profiles/76561198276148059", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "14", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1600516800.0}
