{"text": "So there I was... years waiting for Cyberpunk 2077. Jumping through different titles without being able to find that game that could make me feel something... I thought I was done for. Then one day I discovered it. It changed it all. There I was, watching it as it was being streamed on Steam. I asked myself several times what it was about, it genuinely caught my attention. It was... something different from what I'm used to. I looked at its tempting price... it even had a discount that made me doubt whether to proceed or wait even longer. I decided on the latter. I wasn't sure it was going to offer me what I was looking for. A month later, however, I saw it again as it appeared on the main page. This time there was no streaming to be found. I decided to venture into what others thought of it... but only found concerns that made me hesitate. Consensus was that it was boring, repetitive, that the story was tremendously... unfinished? I hesitated even more as my hands started to shake a little bit. I didn't want to believe it was that bad. ... but I thought people were right. I saw enough good arguments to think about leaving that place for good, not to return... then I said to myself... your experience will never be the same as others... I didn't want to give in into what others said. I decided to accept the idea of giving it a chance. Against all odds I decided I was gonna do it. I bought it without hesitation. ... then I wondered if I had done the right thing. My backlog was huge, I was bankrupt, unemployed because of the damn virus... I had nothing but Mr. Cloudpunk waiting for me... but I didn't give up, I had to find what no game had made me feel in a long time. And so I fired it up. I asked it to give me the time of my life. I know I was asking far too much... I didn't have a choice but to do so. Was it gonna answer the call? I knew they were gonna to. It started... that simple but charming main menu. A great melody in the background that made me feel that every penny would have been worth it. Just the feeling of that song alone made my skin crawl. There I was, under a heavy rain, a HOVA that could barely keep afloat and a coffee by my side. I didn't care. The background music invited me to travel, to explore... to relax from the tensions of the new quarantined life. Going from point A and then moving to B. I wasn't able to ask about the packages... I was supposed to just do the job. What others found disappointing... I thought was entertaining. It was simple yet satisfying. So there I was driving across Nivalis delivering mysterious packages for mysterious even dangerous people. Soon I started to meet more people, androids, automatas, weird AIs... Even someone that I started to love, to appreciate very much. Camus... With several deliveries on my back... I decided I was gonna slow down for a second. This universe was a bit rough and big. I had to explore, so I started to meet even more people. People who had their problems, similar to those of real life, similar to those of me own character. That was when I connected with a game that... felt much more than that. It was complex, something I loved. Soon I realized I had explored almost everything. My HOVA was not a piece of flying junk but a vehicle full of splendor. My carefully decorated apartment... even I had someone new to look after. I had never felt so much responsibility. I had to do my best now that I was not alone. I couldn't risk failing. I wasn't gonna fail to 'em. My hours were increasing, secrets were decreasing, the end was near. My desire not to end was increasing as well. Like everything, there will always be an expiration date. Sadly this was no different. For a few hours, however, I experienced a really interesting story, crazy characters, as well as intelligent ones, or hateful in some cases. I was having the time of my life. For once I was glad I decided to pull the trigger when I had to. I was glad I decided not to believe what other people thought.", "appid": "746850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198073611572", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "444", "votes_funny": "46", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1601726400.0}
