{"text": "Rust is a sandbox online survival game , where your main and only objective is to survive by various ways. Like: crafting weapons, and by forming an alliance. There are many people playing this game daily and for the first sight I must declare: don't play this game if you are a rage-quitter. You will start (most of the times) with a stone and a torch at the beginning. If you level up you can craft or build more things. This game has been made by the creators of Garry's Mod. When you log off and start the game again in a different or the same server, your stats will reset. So if you were level 11 you will start the server again, with the level you was at the begin.  The game is amazing, I already died in the first 3 minutes of playing this game. After reading a guild for beginners I finally understood the purpose of surviving the game: git gud. So I hitted a tree with my stone for gathering wood to build a spear. By hitting the tree you can get 10 woods and some xp to level up. With 300 woods you can craft a spear. When I was finished with crafting my spear, I tried to make a wooden house. But when I was heading towards a tree, I saw a lonely bear and thought that I could beat him for meat. The bear killed me instead like it was nothing.  After a few times of dying in Rust, I was finally ready to beat down some people. I had a house nearby a river, many food, some clothes, and some serious weapons: like a bow. I hunted down a few people and raided some bases. When I was at the top of a mountain in Rust I heard some gunshots nearby from the place I was. I started thinking in myself, shall I head back to my house. So I headed back to my house and saw someone heavily armed running after an animal. I followed him and when he hunted down the animal, I took my bow and tried to aim for his head. But the arrow was shot on his body, he turned in my direction, took his gun and shot me a few times until I was dead.   My impressions of the game. The game is fun, but only if you know the game more than you did in the first time playing. The game has good graphics and good sound. The chat can be somehow annoying and somehow funny. Pros - The game is fun - Many weapons to craft - Different things to build - Different clothes to craft - Open World - Supply drops by planes - Has trading cards - Good graphics - Good sound Cons - No achievements - No clothes at begin - Most of the times no mercy - Hard game for beginners The game is nice and I would recommend you the game, except if you are a rage quitter and will stop playing this game because of dying too much in the game.  Received a free copy for testing/reviewing purposes. This review is part of the Steamified Community Review program. For similar reviews and fantastic giveaways please visit  .", "appid": "252490", "steamid": "profiles/76561198056604889", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "33", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1474977600.0}
