{"text": "YOUropa is an excellent 3D puzzle platformer with clever level & puzzle design that uses the surface-walking M. C. Escher ability well. At first, you are only able to traverse (stick) on surfaces that are flat and rounded. New mechanics (jumping, running, interacting with objects, etc.) are introduced after completing levels that contain electrical wires that power up a gravity like portal. Levels do get progressively harder as you combine these newly learned abilities but never frustrating.  One ability in particular is very helpful as it lets you zoom out the camera to look around the level to find a walkable path to the next objective or to hidden items. There are many hidden items & task that can be done to unlock additional achievements. The paint on your character serves as a health indication where falling off the map, getting wet and taking damage from an enemy slowly removes the paint until there is no more. It is advisable to use a controller which made it easier to move the camera and navigate the map (using a keyboard and mouse gave me a headache which rarely happens in games). Recommended to anyone who enjoys puzzle games [9/10]", "appid": "640120", "steamid": "profiles/76561198068938289", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "51", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1605960000.0}
