{"text": "Rainbow Six Siege is a competitive first person shooter. It has a lot of similarities with other comp-type games,  at the same time it differs significantly.  To begin with, I'd like to say, that R6 relies heavily on cooperation and map knowledge  . One of the main features of the game is destructable environment, you can blow up a wall and shoot your enemy from it, you can destroy the  wooden floor above opponents and much-much more. It brings the gameplay to a whole new level. Knowledge of where to destroy the fortifications is a key to winning.  The game launched on December 1, 2015. With every year, comes a new Season pass. So, whats a season pass ? Basically its your ticket to simplifying the game grind. Why do you need to grind in this game you might ask ? To buy operators ofcourse you silly ! I didn't say anything about operators ? My bad. Yes, this game instead of default playable operators   has Operators with a big O. They have their own story, weapons, gadgets, armor types, speed, abilities   and much-much more. So is this pay2win ? Not at all. Every single operator there is in the game you can buy with in-game currency. Prices on them differ by the release time, older operators cost less, newer cost more. Is it possible to get operators without HARD-GRIND ? Yes oh yes, it is very possible. I was doing that for the first year (I started buying Season passes with Year 2). Like all modern games nowadays this also features cosmetics. There are 2 main types of cosmetics in the game right now: 1- Player skin: Uniform, headgear. 2- Weapon skins: Weapon camo, charm. Most of the cosmetics you can buy with in-game currency as well, but some, for example - Elite uniforms, can only be bought with Silver credits (as I call them), to get Silver Credits you have to pay real money. What are Elite uniforms and why do they cost real money ? Well they customize fully your character: Headgear,uniform, weapon skin,charm, loading avatar, MVP animation, ability skin. This game also features Alpha packs - lootboxes. Wait-wait,there's no need to hate this game for it. IMO, these alpha packs work really good, why so ? Well first of all, you don't need keys to open them, secondly, after each win or loss, you get a spin to get yourself an alpha pack if you didn't get one,  you receive +3% chance of getting it, untill 100% and you get it (after that it drops to 3% again and untill 100% or untill you get it). Can you get Elite skins in Alpha packs ? No. Can You get cool uniforms and legendaries ? Yes, you can. So how does the season pass work exactly ? You have a year, its split into 4 seasons (3 months each), every 3 months - 2 new operators and a map (or map rework) is dropped. You get an addition sale in the store for all in-game purchases with your Gold/Silver credits, you get (0.6 bonus % for alpha packs  . New operators and the map are all free, but with season pass you won't need to buy Operators. You might have noticed that game is 4 years old and still getting bigger and bigger, its all thanks to the dev's and the community that keep this project alive and help it evolve. The dev's said that their goal is to reach 100 operators in-game   with their own set of weapons,gadgets and abilitites. This game is really cool and fun to play, especially if you have 4 more friends to play with you. But as all games this one have its own minuses, some are really annoying tbh. One of the main problems of the game are bugs. Bugs...bugs...bugs... Yes, with every new update,   breaks something, sometimes even they make gamebreaking mistakes. Even with all the fast fixes (some are not fast at all) its still annoying, basically after 4 years in the game you get used to it, but thats not good even a small indie company like Ubi. Second problem is probably very specific. Cheaters, this game has cheaters. Dev's are constantly fighting with them, players are fighting with them as well, but they still keep coming back, probably because of so often sales and free-weekends. Third problem is balance. With all the operators and destructions happening on the map its really hard to balance everything perfectly. With all the player feedbacks e-sports players feedback they keep balancing it. But the problem still remains even  though its being solved. To summon all things said, I would like to say that R6 community welcomes all new players to its ranks. Rainbow Six has born its own community with LOTS of local memes and jokes. In my personal opinion its one of the most if not the most interesting Competitive shooter (and I played lots of 'em). Game has its own minuses, its not ideal, but its still really good and every new game feels like a whole new different experience. I suggest you try this game on frequent free-week's and test it out for yourself. Combining comp-shooter cores with destruction brings gameplay to a whole new level. Myself I have brought tons of my friends to buy it and none of them regretted buying this game. I also met some new friends, all thanks to R6.", "appid": "359550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198028078474", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1503748800.0}
