{"text": "First off, before I explain the review, since everyone has their own personal story about the game, I will also share my story of before and after I pre-ordered the game literally the day after it was announced at E3, I was extremely excited to get the first moments to play the game and essentially get a head start. The beta launch was an absolute â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ up, but even then I thought it could be salvagable. I got to LV 22 before just giving up. The world was incredibly boring, there was no interesting story to keep me invested, and there was a lot of bugs. I didnt touch the game for nearly a year and a half. Then I got it for free on Steam and decided \"what the hell, lets see if anything's changed.\" The game is so much better. Compared to previously, its actually a pretty good game. Let me explain why. PROS: ~The wastelander update added a lot of what the game needed: a proper story. NOBODY really cared about the overseer's story originally, there was essentially NO lasting story, but with the wastelander update, there is an actual purpose, there's an actual reason to care about your actions. ~the new NPCs of the wastelanders, for the most part, are full of personality and color, it feels like real people (or robots), not one dimensional code  with the obvious \"raider\" trope or \"wants to help everyone\" trope ~some of the views are downright breathtaking, even if the game doesnt have the best graphics. You will most often look over a cliff and have a sense of scale, you can see huge buildings and towns that appear as doodles on your map.  ~I absolutely LOVE the idea of the camp, being able to build essentially anywhere you wish as long as it wasnt too close to locations. ~Relatively speaking, there is a LOT of new content in this game even though it uses the same engine as Fallout 4. I saw a review saying that \"This used 90% of Fallout 4's content\", which is absolutely untrue. I say half the stuff in this game are new, there are new armors, new clothes, new weapons, new junks, new textures, new enemies. It is unfair to claim that this is \"basically a DLC for Fallout 4\", just like it is unfair to claim New vegas as \"basically a DLC for fallout 3\" ~I never really had a problem with the atom situation. I feel like with a lot of challenges and achievements of stuff you basically already do, you can accumulate a lot of atoms by just playing the game. Sure, you wont be able to buy EVERYTHING from the Atoms shop, but you can at least buy a decent amount to customize your base and your character. CONS: ~Like any bethesda game, there is a LOT of bugs and glitches, a few of them game breaking, but from my 80 hours of playing, not once did I experience one of those \"game breaking\" glitches, where an NPC steals your gun or someone steals all your stuff from your vendors. I think its just really bad luck to find one of those glitches ~The dialogue can be a little iffy to work with sometimes, not being able to progress, so restarting the entire dialogue, which is annoying ~Fallout 1st is just honestly a terrible idea. THATS just uncalled for in a $40 game. If this game was free, hell, if it was $20, then maybe I could understand that, but thats just dumb, even if it solves a problem I will address next ~The storage limit is honestly tiny late game. at a measly 800 pounds with no way to change it apart from Fallout 1st, you will fill that up REALLY quickly with guns, junk, and things to sell to your own shop. If there was a way to just increase your storage limit permanently, with perk card of atom points, that would be great. ~I'm still a bit iffy on the whole design of repair and scrap kits, they dont change TOO much since repairing armor and weapons is already pretty easy, but its more of a luxury than \"pay to win\" OVERALL: 7.5/10 Since I last played it, this game has improved a LOT. Not a single hacker from experience, no big bugs, and an interesting story. Its starting to feel more like a proper game. When this game came out, I would have given it a 5/10, but I have high hopes for it to perhaps be an even better game than now", "appid": "1151340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198023173016", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1588334400.0}
