{"text": "Nice game. Better with alienware starter pack ^^. . At the starting levels be careful about not to spend more money to repair ( + drone auto-repair ) than you get. . Also focus on not losing your drones which is pure suckage at the start of the game ( as in the time you attack with all your drones by holding down mouse button, you may 'attack' yourself to call all of them back, auto-repair, then fight ). This is also where getting some 5 star drones ( which are tough ) with a giveaway pack means a lot. . Nearly every starter item suck, which is solved only by leveling defense items later on ( you will see the what defence means in this game when you get the 2x defence rune - means everything ). . It takes time to kill tough bosses when their friends are healing them. Attack healers also to stall ( they heal a lot, well the balance in the game is made so that their attacking you is better than their healing any friend ). ( Assuming you had already figured out you have to kill the weakest one first of course, this is for undying triple+ bosses where all of them are big which means may also cost you drones with their long fights. )", "appid": "793490", "steamid": "profiles/76561198047735312", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1557662400.0}
{"text": "First of all, I haven't played AC I or any other episode from the franchise.(Not an AC fan) I can safely say, that AC II was one of the most immersive, enjoyable, compelling and badass adventures I went through as a gamer. A must have in your collection, especially that it is super cheap now. Thanks for reading this!", "appid": "33230", "steamid": "profiles/76561198054793377", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1451476800.0}
{"text": "I am so glad this game has come to Steam at last! I played hours and hours of it on the Xbox 360; felt the calm of acoustic guitars, rolling hills and pigs in tutus, but also ground my teeth, threw the controller, and wept when that little popping sound heralded yet another death. Hey! Remember the one thing everyone remembers about Super Mario Bros. 2? Imagine if that was developed across nearly 200 levels, with a difficulty curve that makes each new level seem possible but also makes you roar with frustration, while managing to remain fun throughout! In short, this is the embodiment of how far a simple mechanic can be stretched, and is a MUST if you are looking for a puzzle platformer like in dayes of olde. It's quaint, fun, addictive and indie. And holy mother of mercy does it get hard.", "appid": "351690", "steamid": "profiles/76561198007331935", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "15", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1493899200.0}
