{"text": "This mod is not for casual playing, but for the player a fan of the role play genre and want a challenge. It fixes and improves on a lot of Skyrims flaws, while keeping the gems we loves from it. Just remember, its still Skyrims engine, so there will be some bugs and crashes that that comes with Skyrims engine. A whole new story with a whole new world, colourful characters and story rich world. Its all a veteran RP'er like me could hope for. From combat to crafting, sneaking around or talking, so much has changed, but is still quite similar. The difficulty curve is certainly noticeable. I played through on a higher difficulty and I got wrecked. a lot. Many enemies are able to one shot you and you will have to use cheap and sometimes \"hateful\" tactics to beat them, but hey, that is part of it. You get into a battle you can't win? Cheap tactic time.  In conclusion, I am in absolutely shocked about how stunning this game and when I played it through, I simply craved more from this world I have gotten so driven by. I know its best to keep it an open ending, but like any good story, it makes me longing for a conclusion, or at least, a follow up. Though for as much as I desires such a thing, i fear it would ruin it for many if there was a set path the story went. And now, as I have finished the game, I am left empty, wanting to have another go, like it was my first time. Dear SureAI. Thank you for this wonderful experience that you have generously given to us. Thanks to the teams and people you've been working with to make it become a reality, to finish it, translate it and upload it. Thanks to the supporters and your devoted fans, who where with you against the odds, i just wish i could have been there from the start to offer my support. And finally, thank you for stealing away over 150 hours into that world which you have created, i enjoyed every minute of it, even when I died over and over. PS, if the developers where to ever make a follow up game, story or another game like this, I would most certainly be looking into it. They have made a fantastic product and I would be willing to pay for a similar experience. Bravo. (Yes, I am aware of their upcoming project: Nehrim: At Fate's Edge and is hoping it is able to live up to its predecessor, even if it is using an older engine)", "appid": "933480", "steamid": "profiles/76561197987147752", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1573300800.0}
