{"text": "This is the kind of VR content I enjoy, so it's an easy recommendation for me.  It takes advantage of the platform, and I particularly like the decision of not letting the player move freely. The puzzles feel refreshing and never overstay their welcome. The puzzles are seamlessly integrated into huge machines, and fixing them allows you to enjoy impressive sequences. The graphics are top notch, and the inmersion is great. I would like to see the devs expand on the concepts, the story, the puzzles and make a bigger game with some improvements.  The game is short, and some may find the price a bit high, so buy it on sale if you must. For me, it's worth the price.", "appid": "408520", "steamid": "profiles/76561198058324910", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1559304000.0}
