{"text": "I ended up buying a Steam controller really cheap in the recent sale and found the perfect game to use it on. Groove Coaster is an absolute blast and it's really satisfying to play. My only complaint is having to play the lower difficulty songs in order to unlock the harder versions, but it's not all lost since the score still contributes to your total leaderboard score.  The visuals were a lot more impressive than I expected and every song feels fresh due to the unique beatmap style. There are a lot of DLC songs to be purchased for those who aren't satisfied with just the base game songs (which total 58 at the time of writing). Do not bother with this game if you're an obsessive completionist as it's not feasible to plan to 100% this game without hundreds, if not thousands, of hours of dedication. I strongly recommend this game to anybody who enjoys rhythm games in both a casual and hardcore capacity. And if you're someone that has a Steam controller laying around collecting dust, this is the best game that comes to try it out on that comes to mind.", "appid": "744060", "steamid": "profiles/76561198036117725", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1575460800.0}
