{"text": "The game isn't very original or groundbreaking, and has a mix of aspects from a lot of different genres, but the end product was still a decent experience. It's also pretty linear, but I found this worked favorably with the design. The powers you control are nice, and combat works really well with them, and it has the basic souls-like qualities, but it's definitely easier than your average souls-like (At least on jedi master difficulty.) Most of the bosses aren't that unique, but some of them were somewhat challenging nevertheless.  The environments are nice, each location being different from each other, and map design in general is good. There are a lot of secrets, and places you only get access to in locations later when you gain new powers, and this made re-exploration more fun. Sadly almost all things you can find are cosmetic, which did somewhat reduce the will to try and look for them. The graphics aren't the best around, but they are still pretty good and decent enough. There weren't many bugs I found, although sometimes you would get stuck at corners which was an annoying experience.  For the price, the game is too short I would say; 21 hours with me exploring most of the secrets and coming back to check areas after gaining new powers, so I did not only focus on the story by any means.  Overall, I'd recommend it if you justify spending the amount it costs (60â‚¬ for me) for only for a roughly 20 hour experience if you don't plan on replaying it anytime soon at least.", "appid": "1172380", "steamid": "profiles/76561198316747508", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1584187200.0}
