{"text": "Clunky and dead.  I don't know which is worse of a option at the top paragraph but I can tell this from the very beginning: Humble Monthly couldn't manage to save this game -as similar as to Rapture Rejects-  I saw the game around first month of 2019, wanted to wait because my intuition told me that the game would be on the monthly or any 1$ / BTA tier bundle. I was not completely wrong, it nearly took 1 year but the game have found it's way in the monthly. It was dead all those months along and is still dead. I just didn't happen to find a match for 20 minutes. Managed to find 2 online matches. I hardly managed to play the game. Controls are just too overwhelming and clunky. It's usually all about running around the map and trying to deliver some good hits with your arms or legs -also you are able to use them in special attacks-. Even though it doesn't sound that bad, trying to control your arms and legs and trying to deliver attacks in the opponent's direction is quite frustrating.  Also, campaign is a mess. I don't expect it to be like EDF but it is just not enjoyable.  Still, if you have a friend who you can play with the game could be a good deal at %80 off or sth around that price or maybe when it is in another bundle. Graphics are nothing breathtaking but kinda cool, wish gameplay could be better but it's still somewhat fun with special abilities and all of those different mechs and different weapons spawning all around the map. If you want a 1 or 2 hours of fun, pick it up. You probably won't get back to the game or try to find a reason to play at all. There are no better options anyway, Gundham Versus is at nowhere better. And, there are definitely no better mech fighting games around this price. Another great example of when the idea is good but execution is bad which leads to fast death of the game(s).", "appid": "709440", "steamid": "profiles/76561198075742770", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1571054400.0}
