{"text": "I rarely leave reviews. I bought the founders pack and tested alpha so I have more experience than most with this game. I had so much hope as I love the survival/open-world/MMO genre. Here is the problem. Nothing is actually that fun in the game. In other MMO's it's worth grinding to get better gear so you can unlock new abilities, mounts, etc. You are grinding to unlock more interesting mechanics that increase the quality of game play. In this game you do un-fun things, to reward yourself with more un-fun things, to go to do more un-fun things. Run up to monster, attack twice, dodge, attack twice, dodge. Get 20-30 meat, run back buy more food. Rinse and repeat. This is a cookie cutter survival game where the only uniqueness is actually a hindrance to game play instead of an addition. This game is just a grind that has no sense of community or attachment to the world around you. I already payed so they already got me, but don't let them get you. Watch one video you will see you've watched them all. Also, how is this an MMO? Nothing you do relies on the multiplayer aspect and there is one class that specifically does melee damage with nearly the same animation for each of the whopping 4 weapons. My biggest problem with this game is that it isn't even CLOSE to what it tried to be and that was consciously not made clear before release. Game tout's PvP and territory battles when that will not be here for YEARS (If the studio really even plans to try to rectify this).  The mobs do not drop anything interesting, there is no sense of surprise in this game. Each monster drops the same thing everytime, no RNG, no rare loot. Just grind to craft everything and then watch durability before you need to go make another because they run out very fast. Just another studio that probably tried their best at the start, realized how hard it is to make a good game. And then went down the path that most studios do. Make a sub-par game and try to make up for it with marketing and community. No community could save this game. If I've learned one thing. It's how to spot games like this in advanced and not get excited. Good games have trailers with actual game play and have dev-blogs that go into the actual game. Not a vague statement/article that gives us no real indication on the direction of the game. -1 for Enplex Games on this one.", "appid": "1239430", "steamid": "profiles/76561198288624119", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1588766400.0}
