{"text": "A while ago, i've been really looking forward to try this game and when i launched it up it was really dissapointing. For me the controls were broken and something seemed really off when i interacted things around the first area. When i tried to open the in-game menu, i had to wait for some reason due to some delay and it really bothered me. Due to the game being broken for me i didn't really have a chance to enjoy it, which was a real shame.", "appid": "418190", "steamid": "profiles/76561198859969196", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1556366400.0}
{"text": "One of the worst 3d anime fighter, period. It's such a shame because the concept is really cool, you have most of your favorite anime characters duke it out with their own iconic movesets. But the game is so fundamentally broken and is unbalanced beyond belief, with lack of gamemodes and with a laughable story that you shouldn't even bother playing through.  So all you are really left with is the fighting itself to rely on, so how is it? It's very simplistic at its core with easy to learn combos, not necessarily a bad thing but the skill depth is definitely missing from here, against good opponents however you can find yourself have a challenge with the timings and counters. This in theory is a perfectly ok/passable fighting system especially for this genre, and it can be fun for a few hours especially with friends.  However there are so many unintentional exploits in combat in which you can't do anything about, and are definitely not scarce in online play. Such as 'guard break cheese' and 'grab into ults' could easily be patched out, but to this day the developers are not doing anything about these issues.  So you have a fighting game with a sh*tty story with cringe cutscenes, no gamemodes and a broken fighting system. What are the positives then? Well, as I said the characters are pretty cool, the game can potentially be fun for a few hours even in online with the right people. And yeah that's kinda it really. Very minor positive I can also give it is that it's partially responsible for making me check out other great shows such as HxH, YYH and City Hunter. So basically game sucks, if there's a major price drop I'd say sure give it a try, but don't get high hopes.  Verdict: 5/10 (It's extremely close to a 4/10, but given how I still find some enjoyement in it, I'll give it a mediocre rate, which still counts as a negative score so it really doesn't matter.)", "appid": "816020", "steamid": "profiles/76561198091867267", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "141", "votes_funny": "27", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603368000.0}
