{"text": "I am updating my review and changing from Recommended to Not Recommended. A long description why will be included. The game is not in a playable state. The release is one of the worst releases in recent history, it is without a doubt the worst of 2020 so far and it is likely it will have been the most trouble-riddled release after the year is over. They decide to release the game at 18:00 (6pm) local time in Nice, where the developers are based, on a thursday. That leaves friday as the only workday before weekend to solve whatever issues arise. Since they release it at 6pm everyone is back from work already and will all try to access the servers at the same time. As you could probably guess this caused a complete server failure. There has currently been more downtime for the online servers than uptime, The _ENTIRE_ saturday has been unplayable. While in game there are a lot of bugs that have caused various levels of problem, from completely ruining your save to being an extreme annoyance, either way things are NOT working as they should. Other than straight up bugs and server problems the game have some serious problems with passive tree balance. Almost all skillnodes in the passive tree that modify damage act as a +% increase, which means it is additive to the base damage. This is a very inefficient way to scale damage. There is almost no multiplicative (more) damage nodes, ONE exists that is literally 100% more damage which basically make the node a must-include in every single build. Due to there almost only being additive damage the only real king of stats for things are +flat damage, +crit and +aspeed. This needlessly makes a large portion of the passive tree a lot worse than it should be and probably a lot worse than it was designed to be. Another issue is stuff like how bow is just straight up across every single metric a worse version of just using pistol. So some balance issues where stuff just dont work great. When it comes to itemization it isnt overly interesting. The Uniques are pretty uninteresting, they arent build defining or really changing gameplay, they're just a lot of stats. Stats themselves are kinda iffy due to above mentioned problems, which makes itemization a weak side of the game currently. The endgame also leaves a lot to be desired. What are the positives? Well the game have a lot of promise. I think in 5-10 months this could have transformed into a very solid ARPG if the devs have stuck with it. I will update my review to recommended when I would feel okay with actually recommending this game to be purchased by a fan of ARPGs. Currently I feel like if I recommended this game to be purchased by someone I would feel very dishonest due to all the issues. I cannot recommend a game based on what it CAN be, I base it on what it is now, and right now this game _cannot_ be recommended.", "appid": "424370", "steamid": "profiles/76561197996342460", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581681600.0}
