{"text": "In \"Don't Sink\" you play as a pirate. You travel from islands to islands and complete quests and delivery jobs. During your journey, you recruit new crewmembers and upgrade your ship. In the sea, you will come across other pirates and random events. It lacks story and depth. You go from islands to islands and defeat other pirates. There you recruit new members and buy supplies. Gain & complete simple quests like delivering supplies form A - B or you must defeat other pirates in this or that island. Conquering existing islands and governing them is made very simple. You need a certain amount of crew members to take over. You can build/upgrade your conquered islands which is the same on all the other islands. Thatâ€™s about it. You do that repeatedly. After some hours you can really feel the grind. The combat is very repetitive. You get attacked by pirates during sailing. In combat, you can either attack, repair or flee by just pressing some buttons (arrow keys) on your keyboard. All encounters are very uninteresting. There is no real player involvement f.e. aiming. The graphics look okay. Though buildings, ships, islands, characters, etc. look all very similar. It felt like I am on the same island/shop and talk to the same people every time. I did quite enjoy it. But there is not much content here. You can finish the game in around 2-3 hours) So I canâ€™t really recommend this game in this state.", "appid": "710610", "steamid": "profiles/76561198256336747", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1530360000.0}
{"text": "I really enjoyed the first Culling since i personally felt it was unique with the healing machines, recycle machines and how it was mainly focused on melee combat and the only way I can recall getting an actual gun of some sort was earning enough points to call in a drop which could be shot down by other players giving them a chance to steal the loot. Culling 2 doesn't have those features, you go into a house and find guns so no more melee focused combat, no healing or recycling machines, I've not seen any crafting not to forget the 'Events' they had in the first game where randomly through the match random events would happen for example the event that made 3 drones holding airdrops come and fly around the center of the map and others, being completely honest just feels like H1Z1 with different graphics so you're better off going to play that", "appid": "752720", "steamid": "profiles/76561198049900256", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "15", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1531224000.0}
