{"text": "Rainbow Six Siege- Let me start with the graphics, the graphics of the game hold up very well despite the gameâ€™s age. The game looks great and it is not that difficult to run even on lower-end hardware. If youâ€™re looking for something like COD or of that nature, youâ€™re going to be disappointed. Itâ€™s a 5v5 team-based attack and defense game. Team communication is pretty critical(Callouts), but you should still be fine playing solo. My complaints about the game is just the slow-paced gameplay. People hold angles for as long as the round lasts and it can sometimes ruin the experience, at least for me. Ubisoft is still updating the game at the time of this review, but the past couple updates have been mediocre at best, Ubisoft has started reusing the same game weapons from existing operators, which might not be a big deal to some but it would be nice to get new weapons with the new Ops. Most new operators have abilities that are not that exciting but thatâ€™s obviously subjective. Of course, I didnâ€™t touch on everything, only the things that stand out to me at the moment, overall it is a simple game, it is easy to learn. I wouldnâ€™t recommend unless you're into this style of slower-paced first-person shooters where team communication is important. If you have 3 or 4 friends to play with then it can definitely be a fun game to play with them. I wouldnâ€™t recommend full price since the game is always on sale anyways but if youâ€™re bored and thinking of a new multiplayer game then definitely give it a shot. Pros -Graphics Still Hold Up -Easy to Run -A lot of Variety for Ops -Constantly Updating -Never Ran Into a Hacker -Never Crashed or Had Problems With Glitches -Easy to Learn Cons -Sound Can be Confusing -Teammates Donâ€™t Use Mics -Ranked System is Still Bad -Lots of Trolls -Uplay", "appid": "359550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198072298786", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1515844800.0}
