{"text": "I am rewriting my review so that it is more so a review of constructive Criticism instead of a review of doubt and disbelief of the game. I now have over 400 hours on farming simulator 2019 i love playing the game but i believe that it has taken a more arcade approach than a simulator approach towards farming i would like to see a physics implemented in the game that allows you to get stuck in mud the more times you drive over the same place i think it also need more features in the machines such as GPS also i think it would be a lot better in my eyes if the pricing of machines and land was a lot more realistic with added features such as the ability to have machines on demonstration of if you can not buy them out right then finance on the specific machine you are looking to purchase. The ability to own land and rent it out to other players on multiplayer also the ability to sell you products that you make such as bales crops or even you machines to others NPC/Players on multiplayer for a more emersive simulator feeling the cost of bills could be a little better also such as road tax insurance etc on anything that is able to go on road as that in my eyes is what a simulator is to simulate life. One more thing i would like to see more info on machine spec such as torque weight etc and the ability to buy new or used machines. It is a good game but not as good as it could be yet.", "appid": "787860", "steamid": "profiles/76561198127822517", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574942400.0}
