{"text": "This is a good looking and well designed game, but its just too difficult.  Some of the levels are extremely long and if you make one mistake you have to start over from the beginning.  There's an \"easy\" mode but it doesn't make it any easier.  If you're a master at platformers, or OK with ragequitting half way through the game, then you should play this, otherwise it might frustrate you. These problems were fixed by the excellent Bit.Trip Runner 2, which has mid-level checkpoints.  For most people, I recommend you play that game first.  If you want more of a challenge, come back and play Bit.Trip Runner.  Its not really a worse or more primitive game, so I don't think there'd be any problem with playing in reverse order.  The first game is just harder and more frustrating.", "appid": "63710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198116443873", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "12", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1505044800.0}
