{"text": "Ah, GTA 5, what to say about this....the good old loading simulator. The first of its kind:D If you enjoy spending half of the time not actually playing the game, but staring at a loading screen - then look no further, this game is for you=)  It doesnt get affected at all by owning a superior pc. Even if you have a NASA computer - you are still looking forward to 5 minutes of loading on each map. There are even free extras like - \"Sorry, its taking longer than usually to authenticate\" and forever classics like \"Timed out loading player data\"...oh boy, oh boy, so many goodies to choose from...just order now, the first 500 buyers will receive a free bucket of lag on the house=)) P.S. As I'm writing this review I cant even log in to the game...along with pretty much all the rest of the pc playerbase :D", "appid": "271590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198008772998", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1580558400.0}
