{"text": "There are a few positive things to say about this game: * Art is of a reasonably good quality. Animations are only a few frames long, though. * Music and sounds are not annoying and there are sound settings in the game. * If you get all the achievements in the game you can copy images and combine them into a picture which is not present anywhere else in the game... or just look at the complete image in the guide. The game itself, though, is an incredibly lazy implementation of a Whac-a-Mole. There's no penalty for misclicks or multi clicks and goal is always the same (click 3 to open a plate, click 5 to finish level). â€œMolesâ€ always appear in the same positions on the 3x3 grid. Clicks on â€œmolesâ€ are often not registered properly. And the entire stage is implemented in the most annoying way possible by forcing you to play 9 mini whac-a-mole games to open image and one more to actually finish it. That's not a challenge, but just an annoying way to prolong the game. Achievements are implemented in the classic spam fashion. Opened in bulks for doing pretty much everything in the game like clicks on previous/next or restart level buttons. Bugs: * Don't open sound settings while whac-a-mole is active - soft-locks the game. * If you open a level with already unlocked girl, select animation in the right menu, go back to level selection screen with CC button and start locked level instead of a static image in unlocked blocks of that level you'll see animation you previously activated. You'll be able to see static images and animation of this level only after finishing it in such case.", "appid": "998930", "steamid": "profiles/76561198024968498", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594728000.0}
