{"text": "I rarely write bad reviews, i like payday and most of the dlcs, but this heists does no deserve a thumb up from me. If you play this map on loud it is ok, pretty bad optimization but playable and enjoyable, the new rocket launcher is nice. But if dare to try this map on stealth it is a complete disaster. Here's why. The spawn point is the worst possible, when you start you have already guards in front of you and you have 2 choiches:  First option, trying to go through them without being noticed, but most of the times you just have to wait that they move out of the way and you loose precious time if you look to finish the map under 13 minutes (for the achievement). Second option: You kill them all, afterall they dont have pager, but half of the time there is a camera in the area and you are screwed right at the beginning. Inside the house. After you hacked the laptop you can finally enter the house, inside this manor you will find an insame amount of guards (with pager) that wont allow you to do a damned step without being noticed, and if you get spotted by one, you are screwed, there is another guard near him for sure. And of course inside the house there is nowhere to hide. Conclusion, I never had any trouble with stealth heists before, most of them can be done solo on the One Down difficulty, with some practice, but this one is seriously annoying. There would be nothing wrong with a map harder than normal but this one is beyond a joke, its totally unplayable and not fun at all. The stealth part need to be reworked, starting from the spawnpoint.", "appid": "548421", "steamid": "profiles/76561198084914322", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1487246400.0}
