{"text": "I really tried my best to like this game because a friend recommended it.  The idea of Split or Steal is to face an opponent across a table and secretly lock in your choice of whether to split the growing pile of coins/money on the table or try to steal it all.  With the money you earn you can buy better costumes and backgrounds used in the game as you stand at the table.  Yep, that is just about it...you just stand at a table.  From the hours I have played it, about 98% of the people choose to split, while a few steal and you have to start over playing, but no worries.  You can build the pot back up to Tier 10 and the maximum amount of coins/money in less than 10 minutes.  There are of course places to pay real time money to buy accessories and perks that build wealth faster, and there are some things you can trade your coins for which will slightly enhance the game, but over all, a one-eyed monkey could play it and probably do just as well.  There is a large chat screen where you can talk to the pool of people who are playing the game, who may or may not talk to you.  You can also join \"org\" of supposedly like minded splitters or thieves.  The only skill in the game is learning to identify who is a thief when you start the round, but once the round starts, you can not back out and just have to guess at what the other person will do.   Even when they send you a friendly message offering to split, much of the time that means they are telling a lie and steal.  In conclusion to my review I can only say that Split or Steal is a game that takes very little brain power. It accomplishes very little other than to build up the \"look\" of your character with a limited number of costumes and effects and gives you the opportunity to message your opponent so that you can lie to and deceive them out of their winnings.  When you steal it lowers your reputation.  There is no actual battle other than just staring across a table and trying to recognize who is is going to split with you or steal from you.  If you both steal, the pot is split and your reputation drops, making you look like a thief.  I have played several different games on Steam during the last 15 years, including nearly 14,000 hours on TF2, but I have never seen a more useless and mean spirited game than Split or Steal.  If you enjoy being mean, having people be mean to you and like to lie and deceive,  then you might rate this game higher, but for me, on a scale of 1 to 10 I would give it a 2 at best.  Yes, I know it is only a game and it is free to play, but if this is all there is to it, then why bother playing it?  I rank it as the worst game I came remember ever playing.  Bird Of PrAy {toj.cc}", "appid": "1162930", "steamid": "profiles/76561197978865617", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1588852800.0}
