{"text": "Kinda a pile of poo game. Dont be expecting Rainbow Six Vegas 3, or a game like any of the older predecessors because this is far from a Rainbow Six game, it has more in common with Overwatch and Counter Strike. People talk about how much this games changed sense launch, and it has but not for the better unless you count loot crates and micro transactions as progress. On the other side of things some stuff... hasn't changed at all! I honestly don't understand how people are okay with a five year old game having literally one game mode... 5v5 attack and defend... that's it! That's all you will be doing. At least counter strike supports way more people (64 people), mods with tons of game modes, maps you can remember (seriously all the maps are so bland they all just blur together into a single destroyable house of mediocrity)... lets not forget the once novel idea in multiplayer video games of being able to pick the friggen loadout/gun you want is now gone and replaced with the lovely new method of dividing all the in game content behind  50+ \"unlockable\" characters that will each requires 4-10+ hours of grinding to get with in game currency (or just bust your wallet out and shell more money at the game). The core game play and mechanics are fun but idk why this game gets as much praise as it does, is this really what people want in modern video games? The in game community has so many little squeaky kids, so you have to turn the ingame voice chat off right away. It doesnt end there because its a super toxic community, for example god forbid your friend doesnt want to instantly shell out  more money for the game they just bought... Well that's fine they can play the only character available for the first 4 or so hours of the game... the recruit... well great!!! because now they will get vote kicked at the start of every round because clearly their a scrub!!! Oh things you would get in the older titles (beyond 5v5 attack and defend) that are no were to be seen in this game. A full campaign, that could be done solo (with ai squadmates) or co-op (with ai squadmates). A actually fleshed out terrorist hunt mode (its in this game but called \"practice mode\" and not a single souls playing it online... ive checked) yes a fleshed out terrorist hunt mode!!! The old game let you pick the map you wanted to play on (Crazy idea right) and let you pick enemy density, and time limits, have ai companions allowing you to play the modes solo, as well as a few other basic options  (all of which siege is missing). I give this game a 4/10, its core gameplay and mechanics are great. But atleast for me, it got boring real quick... what little content the game can offer you beyond 5v5 attack and defend is locked behind microtransactions and a miserable community/experience.", "appid": "359550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198000876955", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594123200.0}
