{"text": "A game seemed to be riddled with lag infestation and \"extra\" content. Most if not 80% of the content of the game is from expandable purchases, which are not cheap. To support such a game I would hope that it would; 1. Run smoothly. 2. Look appealing. 3. Be fun and balanced gameplay. 4. Have interesting storylines. 5. Have some longevity with friends and end game goals. However from what I've seen this is mostly not hitting any of these brackets. The game has much internet lag and performance on new content maps and areas is lack luster. Especially for the graphic design style, I'd expect more.  Character models and scenes are washed out, it seems to be going for a darker fantasy Elder Scrolls experience however, the tone may be in the right place but the molded textures and meshes with lacking color and intriguing design work on outfits, scenery, weapons, and even lots of the animations are outdated. I wouldn't have bought the series if I didn't enjoy the storylines and lore of the Elder Scrolls, and this online experience with friends exploring the world is actually a cool idea that Fallout 76 seemed to tank on. This alone tho is not peaking my interest and the game overall is really just a bland experience with not many leading innovations to keep my patience on development time.", "appid": "306130", "steamid": "profiles/76561198030795262", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1590494400.0}
