{"text": "Even though this is an RPG Maker game, I was actually enjoying it until I encountered the game breaking bug that another reviewer mentioned. On Day 4, your character is automatically walking a girl home.  After exiting the subway, the girl walks over to the lamp post, but because there is an NPC near the subway entrance that is in your way, you are stuck.  This NPC only turns around and does not move from his spot, and you cannot control your character at this time.  I couldn't even open up the menu to save/load/quit.  You literally can't do anything. Until the devs fix this (which isn't likely, since the review pointing this out was made over a year ago and it isn't fixed yet), this game gets a thumbs down from me.  Would love to continue it, but at this time that is not possible.", "appid": "562640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198032080092", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "14", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1530360000.0}
{"text": "I was given this for free to share with my community. While I do love survival horror games, this one was just way to short. I did get a few jump scares and had some creepy feelings while playing, the game is simply not long enough. Once you learn it you can finish it in about 10 mins. It took me 30 since I blew myself up lol. Graphically game looks amazing and the sound quality is really good, however there is just to much of a lack of content for me to really say it is worth it. Hopefully they add more to the game because this would be awesome with more. You can see my game review and playthrough here:", "appid": "1043350", "steamid": "profiles/76561197999298310", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1555675200.0}
{"text": "First of all. I got this game for free. And it's HORRIBLE. First, the menu is an abomination. Second, it's a mess of default unity assets mixed up with one of the worst AI I've ever seen. It's a total nonsense. The song is a free rap song I heard a while ago, that loops over, and over, and over. It gets annoying after the third loop. The blood splatters are EXACTLY the same blood sprites I found on google some months ago, and I used them for a photoshop job I had to do for my school. You can walk THROUGH windows (Non-destroyed windows. With the glass and everything), the ammount of glitches is amazing (I saw a plane flying sideways while dropping some crap), and the worst of all: It's a generic damn shooter. You can clearly see that the developer placed NO effort onto this game. The netcode is horrible. The zombies, if you can call them that way, are damn weak. ANY weapon kills them in one hit. Aside, what the hell? There's like a nazi general zombie, a mime-like zombie, and other sprites that look a lot like the sprites you can download for free to add on any game. I dare to say even a 10-12 year old kid can make a better game than this, in just a few hours. This game, is one of the few games I really hate. This, is from my point of view, even worse than bad rats. I mean, bad rats is WAY more enjoyable than this game, with it's cheap 60's porno music and bad physics. Even if I got this for free, I demand a refund. Oh, and strangely, almost every positive review come from accounts that have just one review, and luckily, one game. This game is a mess. 0/10 EDIT: This review is disliked by 1 person only. I'm sure it's the dev.", "appid": "329950", "steamid": "profiles/76561198039292424", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "49", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1424347200.0}
