{"text": "BAD END isnâ€™t absolutely awful and for its price it isnâ€™t an eyesore in your library but there are far better choices out there. However if you care about achievements, this should be an easy way to get another 100%. + Short + Fascinating premise + â€˜Skipâ€™ works flawlessly - Dumb protagonist -  Cliche, unoriginal twists  â˜†â˜†â˜†â˜†â˜†â˜†â˜†â˜…â˜…â˜…  3/10 - Bad This visual novel simply didnâ€™t live up to the interesting premise it set up so Iâ€™m forced to give a bad rating to BAD END. While it wasnâ€™t completely awful to sit through, there simply isnâ€™t anything too engaging or memorable about the whole experience. The protagonist is so unrelatably idiotic in getting himself into the mess that itâ€™s just hard to care about him surviving through all of it and it becomes more fun to see how many ways is there for him to die.   It needs to be mentioned that the player is presented with choices to make the protagonist less dumb but these bring the story to an end and thus are not correct choices. It is understandable that with a premise like this there needs to be something driving the protagonist to go through with it, but in this case it feels too feeble of a reason what is given to work here. The story offers no surprises and the supposed big twist is painfully obvious. The characters are uninteresting and it feels strange that some seem to have been inserted just to create an illusion of bigger cast. On a more positive side, the art is okay and BAD END plays well, itâ€™s very easy to go through it multiple times since the â€˜Skipâ€™ function makes it effortless. There are several choices and they (for the most part) lead to different types of outcomes, but it seems like there shouldâ€™ve been more â€œrealâ€ endings rather than just a ton of dead ends. But with a name like BAD END, what else would I expect?", "appid": "415850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198319223099", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false