{"text": "The game itself is great, but the Steam version comes with ridiculous limitations. First off, there is an activation limit, which from what I know, is not revocable. The Steam version is only the 32-bit version, no 64-bit available. It's buggy at some places and crashes often. Many people report the game not even starting at all, despite me not having this problem on a 64-bit machine. Windows 10 users are especially affected. You can get around the bugs and crashes with community patches, but that is already a minus if you need community-made patches to get the game run correctly on steam. So, please, get the retail version of this game, the steam version is not worth the pain. EDIT: After I have been provided a link to the 64-bit binaries for Crysis, the game has been running stable now. It is not guaranteed that it will work, but it should fix some issues for 64 bit users. This fix is useful if your game is refusing to even run. Link can be found in the comments, last page", "appid": "17300", "steamid": "profiles/76561198045216527", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "34", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1471262400.0}
