{"text": "I'm a long time fan of the series ever since the first game in 1991, but this is a major, major, disappointment on the technical side. Let me begin with the BAD things first. NetherRealm Studios somehow broke this game. I have over 1600 games in my library and absolutely NO OTHER GAME crashes as much as MK X. MK 9 for example runs flawlessly.  THE BAD: In the first week of the release it had massive bugs, and also had massive patches to fix some of the issues, with updates over 15gb. The game still suffers from a bad memory leak problem which happens every so often, after 2-3 hours of gameplay. That is a bit upsetting but I managed to finish the game story and it was all fine, Krypt mode was fine, local versus was fine.  The really BAD thing is when you start to play online and try to have fun with friends, or perfect your fighting skills. All the recent patches the game received so far did nothing to help as well. I absolutely CAN'T complete a single online fight, either on KOTH mode, any rooms or single online versus. Crashes happen every time, and sometimes on character select screen or a few seconds into the fight, either with a black screen or simply the game freezing and not responding. And yes, I've tried a clean reboot, rolling back Nvidia drivers, rolling back PhysX drivers, reinstalling DX versions and everything else from scratch. Absolutely nothing I've done worked.  I will change this review at a later time when NetherRealm fixes this mess. Some friends report problems, others do not. It's really a hit and miss, depending on your system. Then again, an AAA game of this magnitude shouldn't have these issues, not by a long shot. As reference, I'm using a very good setup, i7, 16gb ram, gtx 980. THE GOOD: The story of the game is a retelling (with a bit of retconning) following the demise of Shao Khan a few years later and the plot that follows sometime after MK3. Graphics are very well done, gameplay is improved but still familiar for those coming from MK 9 / Injustice, and the game has a lot to offer for both old and new players. Story is a bit shorter than MK 9 but satisfying, and sets up a few twists and questions for future games. Each fighter has 3 different styles, and as a general rule the variations cover rushdown/turtling/zoning. It's down to what style you like the best, and which one best counters the opponent's. You'll spend quite some time exploring the Krypt and unlocking some content for the game, while the rest you'll acquire playing the game, using each character many times and on the special hourly/daily/weekly towers, living towers and other future Invasion / Boss events. CONCLUSION: With all this said, I would recommend you to get the game if you really like the series, and see where the story goes, but it's not yet perfectly optimized for online play and you could have problems depending on your setup, with known bugs which have yet to be fixed. It pains me really as a fan to say this, but I will not recommend it at this time if you like a solid and smooth online experience.", "appid": "307780", "steamid": "profiles/76561198007123604", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1431691200.0}
