{"text": "This DLC is just terrible. New biom is kinda cool and refreshing but it's just a big city with a lot of buildings you can destroy. It offers some new tactical options but that's it. I'v been playing for a while but I didn't had a chance to get new mechs or gear. New mission type is just a waste of time. I just played one of difficult 3 with my lance or 4,5 rateing. I gave up. At some point enemy had something around 10 or 12 mech on map and 4 more incoming. It's not just factory producing new units, enemy get's 3 waves of reinforcements fromt he sky and I didn't even had turrets defending my base. That's just stupid. Certainly don't pay 20$ for this DLC, it's not worth it and very dissapointing. But after playing Roguetech mod vanilla game will always be disappoiting for me now.", "appid": "1047180", "steamid": "profiles/76561198022897265", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "25", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561464000.0}
