{"text": "-The gameplay itself feels choppy and poorly paced. Not only does it feel like you are on a monorail with how you move about the cases, this kind of game really benefits from the third person perspective so you can get an overarching view of your crime scenes and work from there. Being in first person just doesn't feel right to me. -The minimum graphics settings made driving and reading for me nearly impossible. I literally could not see the key that I was supposed to turn. If I didn't have LA's layout memorized l would have gotten lost as I could not see the road in the dark.  -As someone with 12 years of experience in hand to hand combat, I can say the fistfights are cool. However, the game seems more inclined to register a block only if the incoming punch connects with your elbow or wrist. This alone makes the game less immersive as trying to reach out and block the punch without directly shielding your face is more difficult than your arms make it seem. Note that indeed your arms are actually there in the world.  Overall, If you have a lower end VR card or aren't that interested in the game: Pass on it.  If you have a higher end VR card (as of right now I would only suggest the 1080ti) that can actually use supersampling, I would suggest giving it a try. The short time the game let me run S.S. before frameskipping a lot was much more enjoyable. my most major turn off was the fact that it felt like i was blind walking around.", "appid": "722230", "steamid": "profiles/76561198100468893", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1516795200.0}
