{"text": "4/10 Graphics â˜ Beautiful â˜‘ Average (Can look good in places, but lens flares can ruin the colour at times) â˜ Outdated Gameplay â˜ Very Fun â˜‘ Average (if it wasnt for the scoped kar98 i would have given it a lower score) â˜ Repetitive  Audio â˜ High quality â˜ Average â˜‘ Poor (While the ost is actually pretty good, the mixing of sfx and voice is very poorly done) Difficulty â˜ Very Hard â˜‘ Average (On highest difficulty, Ai make it very average in terms of challenge) â˜ Too Easy Story â˜ Amazing â˜‘ Average (Voice acting helps with the story, but i never felt very engaged) â˜ Low quality Bugs â˜ None â˜‘ A Couple (Ai pathing is poor, often getting stuck, I also go a couple of crashes in loading screens) â˜ Gamebreaking Bugs Pros -Graphics & Lighting are quite nice, as well as certain texture maps are good (not all) for a 2014 title. -Level design is good, great architectural detail and scaling, the shaders and textures help with this a great deal. -Decent voice acting, nothing revolutionary but it does the job, conveying a realistic story. -Some Levels are quite open ended, giving the player a less boxed in feeling, (some are still quite linear though). -Loading screens while quite obvious, are nicely done with a moving freeze frame showing the upcoming mission.   Cons -Poor Ai, they feel incredibly dated, their detection to player movements seems more based on the stealth metre than an actual programmed detection system, as they just don't react in a smart way, all instantly seeing player behind walls if detected. more 2007 than 2014 standard for comparison i just came from Frontlines fuels of war and that had better ai and it's from 2008. -Clunky controls, everything from weapon reloads/ads, crouch, running, vaulting & takedown feel slow and unresponsive. As if the player is sliding on ice, very old programming style, doom comes to mind (lol). -Very Lack-luster audio mixing, From muddy overpowering bass which destroys voice clarity which is sad as the voice acting is actually fairly decent and footsteps, to certain sounds cutting off. e.g smgs if select firing them, very amateur mixing. even with a sound edit on my end can't seem to clean it up. -The UI, dear lord... not sure where to start with this one, it looks like an alpha placement. it should have been scaled to 50% the size for starters as the textures are both blurry and low res (540p?), and moved from the middle of the screen. it seems scaled to a 5:4 ratio for some reason. I am playing on a 21:9 UW, but i dont think that's the reason its so close to the middle, its def not 16:9 scaling. -Alt+Tab doesn't seem to work, so if you ever crash you would need to relog. -Sound effects are inconsistent, carpet sfx sound the same as grass? not sure what to say about this, other than not sure what they are thinking. -No prone, this for me is something i do actually use in fps sp games at times, especially a stealth fps. -End of missions end very abruptly, as in they just cut to a loading screen almost mid sfx, feels like an alpha like they forgot to edit a fade out or something. -Checkpoints, if you do happen to die on the rare occasion. Can be quite bad, setting you back 10 minutes of play if you were doing stealth etc. -Facial animations seem very robotic & janky.  'Brief' Summery Enemy Front is a FPS ww2 shooter, set mainly in the setting of a splinter group of Polands resistance force, against the Nazi occupation of Warsaw, Poland. While the setting, missions, and Level design are all well thought out and structured, the gameplay is very low tier holding back any potential this game was trying to accomplish. They Ai are Incredibly dumb at times, failing to notice you, or getting stuck in doorways, poor pathing. By the end of the game i felt good to be done with it, very little to be desired here, definitely one of the worst ww2 shooters iv'e played in recent years. There is a Dlc bonus mission, again fairly forgettable but still had alright pacing, placed in the role of a British soldier     (i think?).  If like me you like to try games with low acclaim but hidden great aspects, THIS is NOT it there are little to no redeeming features, not recommended unless bought on a deep-sale. Im usually fairly forgiving in my criticism of games, but 'experience' this really didn't sit well with at all. Take that as you will. Time Played Hours: Story: 6 Completionist: 10+", "appid": "256190", "steamid": "profiles/76561198060434019", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "12", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598443200.0}
{"text": "I bought this back in 2011. It's still nowhere near finished and updates are few and far between. It's abandonware; do not buy. Have to edit this because people have poor reading comprehension.  The game wasn't always on Steam, and I put in plenty of time back when it was getting a good amount of updates (2011-early 2013). Ever since then the game has hardly changed at all, and arguably the earlier versions were a lot better.  The latest update (build 40 as of writing this) was released 30th October 2018. Build 39 was released on May 31st. That's 4 months for a single major update. Now you must be thinking, wow it must have added a lot? Nope, it took them 4 months to add some rain and make some changes to how the character feels temperature.  This is the running cycle of these updates. Months apart with what feels like very little change. Most of the good content that should've been in the game by now was provided by modders. They even went and took mods to save them the effort of doing some actual work on the game.  It's abandonware, plain and simple. Much like many games released on EA, don't expect this to release any time soon.", "appid": "108600", "steamid": "profiles/76561198021603755", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1541073600.0}
