{"text": "i really want to like this game but after some of the experiences i had with it, i decided not to, the game is physics based and thats really cool, however said physics engine is far from enjoyable, the game uses a reverse kinematics skeleton to see where your limbs and body are supposed to be, with that said, alot of the movements that i was able to do in real life are very restricted in game, either i cant aim properly or hit things because of the characters paralysed wrist that makes your arm look weak holding a crowbar, did i mention that your wrist wobbles and bends around when you hack enemies. On to the firearm combat, its very moderate, sure the physics is a fresh aspect, but you have to reload with another mag, i meant you hold a mag next to your gun for the empty mag to fall out on to your fresh mag clipping the physics and thats 3 more seconds wasted in intense combat with holograms balls. Also dont forget the mag holder is right next to your left armpit holster, that means when your rifle runs dry, your emergency secondary pistol would instead be a fresh mag * might appeal to some*. Forget about vaulting things, because your legs are crippled as well, making scaling over objects slower than my grandma does it. Oh and my hatchet clips through the â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ floor once in a while. Now on to the story aspect, it has no clear storyline, why? because the in game world called MythOS is a work in progress, the developers jammed random textures and objects in to the game, its a literal Gmod server / halflife / portal wannabe. It feels like the dev decided to used prototype object and ai to build the world while adding more detailed objects as their skills in CAD improves.   after my rant, its still a fun experimental game, but i cant take neither the story nor the characters nor the physics seriously, because its just, unsatisfactory and frustrating", "appid": "823500", "steamid": "profiles/76561198144719896", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1591272000.0}
