{"text": "Gotta give a thumbs down for this game now, the game is GOOD Il give it that, but like all VR games (Why cant there be a perfect VR game :L) this has problems for one, they introduced screen mode which means that players can get an unfair advantage in certain activities, most notably Dodgeball (screenmode in dodgeball is outright broken as Ive seen playing with a friend who was using it), Dodgeball itself is also the worst game in Recroom, so bad that the devs have to force people just to play it through the medium of weekly challenges which is a good idea... I guess but why on earth does the reward for weekly challenges always suck! This weeks prize (as of writing) is like a wood camo for the 3 shot paintball rifle... Yay... I earned that camo back when it was first distributed... and it's been at least 4 times since its shown up! (from what Ive seen!) I already have the camo! Cant I get a different prize? or better yet currency so we can just buy weapon camos outright? They made a shop for the game which let's you buy clothes and stuff, which is cool I guess, but there's NEVER anything that I wanna buy, I probably have a huge bank of currency to spend... Most of the activites are great but ALWAYS have one major flaw with them... Paintball has atrocious hit detection and overpowered grenades that can hit through cover, same with Lazertag which is outright abused, Quests are fun as hell... If you have a Team that doesnt consist of filthy casuals (cause theyre far too hard for ordinary players to complete and gain any fun from them) Dodgeball doesnt even follow real life rules of dodgeball but it doesnt matter cause the hit detection is questionable as well as screenplayers simply being able to spam the grab button to catch incoming balls extremely easilly. And all the other games... good luck getting some players to actually play them with you unless the devs are forcing players to play them like shield soccer and dodgeball... The devs have tried to coverup the fact that you can segregate true VR players to screen players but what they dont tell you is that to do that you have to click on a seperate activity listing which is MUCH harder to find than the main one which puts them all together, and when you find it, good luck getting some players to join ya :L Honestly while it's a good idea to introduce screen players to the game (People too poor to afford VR) they should have just waited for VR to mature then monetise the currency in the game (Which is what I think they're gunna do anyways) But I noticed like a poll asking what platforms Rec room should be ported to and things like the Nintendo switch were on the list and im just like... the Nintendo switch... Seriously? Once a VR game, now a mundaine free to play activity game... If that day arrives, Il find something else to play.", "appid": "471710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198041405506", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1549540800.0}
