{"text": "first let me start, I play offline mostly, so my time is a bit off. So I was excited to get this game, and I had little expectations on how Hanbitsofts version as I had never played global, only the original release by flagship (I have the original copy). I figured, why would I not want to support this, its an underrated game that I want to see succeed. After playing this version I started to get the dreaded 1FPS bug. tried all the fixes ppl suggested, nothing worked. I waited for Hanbitsofts patch, they finally released and the only thing they suggested for the bug was... meeting minimum requirements to run it. Now ok, maybe they are just not paying attention, and with enough ppl complaining they will fix, as they were planning on releasing Tokyo portion. When that released, they did not even mention the bug, nor did they try and fix it silently. The issue is still there. As of this point in time, Hanbitsoft has not said a peep since they released Tokyo. This tells me there is no desire to make this game work like it should. I have stopped trying for now, and would only come back if by a miracle they do fix it. That being said, I have my original DVD, and with all the community patches, I dont have to worry about the bug. Seriously, everything else about this version, were all minor annoyances, the change of language, multiplayer things still in for it being a single player game, not an issue, its just the bug that needs fixed, all else is not game breaking. But do I recommend, no, not really. at least not any version by Hanbitsoft. If the bug was fixed I would, as it is a really good game, for now, if you REALLY want to play it, spend about 15 bucks and get a used copy on Amazon. there are community patches that can fix the bugs and its a real gem of a game.", "appid": "939520", "steamid": "profiles/76561197975117880", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1547726400.0}
