{"text": "Poor gameplay that never feels fluid, an irritating running commentary by a character we're never sure who he is or why we should care about him, absurd difficulty spikes, and a horrible final boss and ending. Bastion is one of my favorite gaming experience ever, so there was never a possibility where I wasn't going to buy and play SuperGiant's next game. So with that in mind I won't say I wish I hadn't played it. I just wish I could have appreciated the incredible visuals and fantastic soundtrack without the gameplay and narration constantly interrupting and getting in the way. The entire length of the game I felt like the gameplay was working against me. Every ability you have can be combined in different ways and then used in combat either real time or by pausing the game and choosing a sequence of actions to set up and then have executed automatically. Interesting idea, but the way it was implemented I could never find a good balance. Either I was using an ability combo that absolutely trivialized the encounter to the point where it was boring, or I was getting my butt kicked with little opportunity for me to recover. The gameplay always hovered between mildly frustrating and jaw-clenchingly irritating. There's nothing wrong with a game being five hours long, which is how long it ended up taking me to beat it. A game that short can have a lot packed into it to make it an incredibly worthwhile experience. Transistor doesn't have that, though, and in fact started to outstay its welcome before I had even gotten to the final areas. The final boss is a terrible mess of a gameplay mechanic completely unlike the rest of the game, forcing you to come up with new strategies on the fly and learn new ways to approach the game. The ending, which I will absolutely not spoil here, was right in line with the rest of the game in that it was a frustrating kick in the pants that was completely unearned.  It's confusing, frustrating, irritating, absolutely gorgeous, and has an incredible soundtrack. Unfortunately those last two don't make up for the rest.", "appid": "237930", "steamid": "profiles/76561197972662016", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1400587200.0}
