{"text": "Same old \"Repetitive\" Tomb Raider.. just in a slightly different environment.. and yet in a similar environment. If you liked those previous Tomb Raider games, you certainly won't dislike this one either. Same gameplay, similar story as previous ones, similar settings just a few more stealth ways to kill enemies like stealth takedown from mud walls.. rest is all same. Graphics are definitely improved. Overall a solid game on par with other modern games. The reason i don't recommend this is bcoz you're paying for basically the same game again.. nothing really has changed from the previous Tomb Raider except for the graphics improvement, it's the same as what you've played in those previous TR games. No special reason to buy this \"NEW\" Tomb Raider.. You can't even say that the setting of game is different from previous ones as you'd find in those AC games. Setting is also the same as older ones. If you're new to Tomb Raider, then just buy Old Tomb Raider game.. then if you really love it so much that you're willing to spend more money to play the same game again with a slightly different story then it's your choice. There's no special reason for me to recommend this repetitive game. It all depend on you.", "appid": "750920", "steamid": "profiles/76561198824257714", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1575028800.0}
