{"text": "At this point the game is really weak and doesn't appeal to me the way the older paradox titles do, even though it takes place in one of my favorite time periods. Just like its predecessor \"Europa Universalis: Rome\" it captures both aspects of CK2 and EU4 but does quite a bad job by trying to do so. I'm not even complaining about the AI which is incapable in every paradox game but rather the whole way the game turned out. Worse battle mechanics than CK2 and worse Grand Strategy and Mana Point implementation than EU4.  This game will probably need two years of patching and $200 of DLCs in order to make it enjoyable, which is quite disappointing and yet for paradox addicts like me an expected and  accepted practice...  With worries I waite for Victoria 3 ever since I got my 1000 hours on Vic2, but when I look at the recent titles (HOI4, Stellaris and now Imperator: Rome), I do not even want to think about what that game will end up looking like.  I can only appeal to Paradox to revert the current trend and again try to capture what the old but gold games like Darkest Hour, Crusader Kings and Victoria 2 were doing and stop investing in fancy graphics, bigger maps and overloaded interfaces, which all do not contribute to the real enjoyment and replayability of those games.", "appid": "859580", "steamid": "profiles/76561198006547614", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "18", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1556366400.0}
