{"text": "I am writing early but as I have played the discord release and beta a year back I think I can write enough about this release at this point.  My first problem comes with how the Killer and survivors are chosen. The system this game uses is similar to Dead by Daylight, where you can choose to go Killer or survivor and you are placed in lobbies as such. There are 2 problems with the way this game does it.  Number 1: if you have a friend with you, you cannot play as Fiend at all or you don't earn EXP or progression. You are forced to play solo if you want to play as a fiend. In Friday the 13th, it was randomized who became Jason with preferences, so everyone could play together and not be punished for it.  Number 2: This game does not have Dead by Daylights playerbase, so if too many people want to be killer, then matches take forever to start. This is in addition to the fact the servers are region locked, so your pool of players is even less then what Steam's data tells you. With Friday the 13th, anyone could join and there were no restrictions and queues for specific roles. Now for the basic gameplay, my 2nd issue is the scrap system. It is very very annoying to be grouped up and having everyone swipe scrap that you desperately need to craft weapons to protect yourself. This promotes people to separate so they can collect scrap without dealing with people swiping it away from them. This means the survivors are more isolated for the Fiend to easily take them down. Since there is no communication or signals beyond standing still to type out your words, letting yourself be open to an attack, players are overwhelmed by Fiend in most cases due to scrap allocation and no signs to communicate well. You don't need voice chat to fix this issue, just do what at least a dozen other games do and use a call out system. Finally, there is no tutorial or basic information on how to play, beyond that ton of HUD clutter that pops up at the beginning of every match that you have all of 5 seconds to comb through before being thrown into the rush of the match. When and if you even get into a match, you are given 0 information outside of what buttons to press to do what. Anyone playing the game for the first time would have no idea they are supposed to craft weapons and tools with R and many Survivors get blown out and have a bad experience. That bad first impression is all it takes to scare off most of the potential playerbase, leaving only a small group behind.  I'm also annoyed by the entire spellbook system, since everything is single use consumables, and most of the starter spells are absolutely worthless for any new player while the good ones are locked behind an insane grind like rescuing 50 classmates to unlock one section. The live service model they've used is never going to work, considering this game is not big, and nobody wants to grind for a 2nd job while a dozen other AAA titles are asking for the same amount of work. It's just a terrible experience for everyone.  Most of this can be fixed easily, but that first problem I have is never going to be changed since it is built into the design of the game and not a problem to the dev team. There are other problems too like no voice chat, no dedicated servers, fiends camping escape door, the time limit, etc. but those can all be fixed in time. Just hold your money for a few months.", "appid": "1195460", "steamid": "profiles/76561198011672203", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1575979200.0}
