{"text": "Ill start at the top. It is a reskined version of Ark:survival evolved (It took out dinos and added pirates...) The game takes forever to load and once it did I had a 50/50 chance it would glitch/crash. (Ark is WAY more stable!) The food system requires 4 different kinds of food to keep you healthy not all of which are readily available and if you eat too much of one kind it will quickly kill you. Its called Atlas so when you google things on it you get a ton of travel sites. (didnt think that one through) Every time I went to a new region the game crashed and often crashed when I reloaded it. got lucky a couple times and got to continue my adventure. (the load time and the glitch/crash possibility alone make this game unworthy of purchasing) You die, a lot, and for stupid reasons. Pretty much all the claimable land is taken on all the public servers so you can only really play the game solo or find a way to join the clans that are already monopolizing the servers. The game is huge and if you want to run it at full graphics you will need a top end gpu. Dont buy this game unless you like being angry all the time.", "appid": "834910", "steamid": "profiles/76561198111990191", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1578830400.0}
