{"text": "Not what i was expecting. My first thoughts going in to this game were positive: Nexon are bringing back the old game. But the moment i started playing it i realised i made a mistake donloading it. In my opinion Nexon is well know at this \"free\" 2 play genre and once again they did a \"good\" job. An old clasic on which many gamers spent hours and hours just got worse than it's first days. Even though they used the same engine my old config didn't worked, they added more resolution options but the crosshair would stretch as well so you can't really aim at anything. I know that i didn't spen a lot of hours on this game ant that it might be \"early\" release but i just could't resist writing a review on how this game is not worth playing. To sum it up i will write all cons and pros. -Pros: *Old classic *Lobbies and modes *More weapons ( more equipment to use ) *Anyone can play at native resolution *Almost the same engine -Cons: *More weapons ( you need to craft/buy them ) ( some are way overpowered: as an example pistol with zoom can 1hs you) *Poor performance ( you can find a game very quick but the game wouldn't go past 71 fps ( not capped) while i run CS:GO at 300 *Issues with windowed menu *I ran in to hackers second day *Old setings doesn't work *It doesn't feel like cs 1.6 ( the guns handle diferently) *Different zombies must be bought. I think that I listed most of the things that came to me in a couple of hours. Playing more might change my opinion, but I won't give it a chance because on the other hand i think that playing more will just ruin everything i kne about 1.6 and this game will become even worse.", "appid": "273110", "steamid": "profiles/76561198027880127", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1412856000.0}
