{"text": "Once again a huge AAA title with good graphics and attention to detail, but disappointing in every other aspect. I will try to keep it the review as slim as possible, so let's dig into the pros of the game first. Don't worry, they aren't many. + Great attention to detail (as I said in the beginning). The world is full of wildlife, the vegetation is diverse. The cities are bustling with life, the people are always doing something - they broom their property, talk to each other, smoke, drink, play cards; there are small animals like cats and dogs, it's just so nice and comfy. + The scenery is very beautiful. What I really appreciate is that each area you go through feels completely different and has a unique atmosphere, attached to it. Jungles, forests, snowy mountains, beaches, you have it all. + Amazing voice-acting on Arthur Morgan. The main character is pretty decent, to be honest. + You can grow a huge beard and have a cool hat. Well... To be honest I was expecting the pros to be a little more than that, but truly I don't see anything else that would classify as a 'pro'. Let's see what's up with the cons. - Incredibly slow and mundane gameplay. I understand that the game is meant to be enjoyed slowly, but it's too much. I thought Red Dead was a game, where you are supposed to rob trains and banks and cause chaos. However, most of the missions are just a long-ass stroll with a bit of gunnin' here and there. The looting animations are sooooooooooooo slow, too - it takes ages looting a pile of bodies or skinning an animal. - Pretty much a non-existent story. Basically, you're a part of a gang and do errand-boy stuff, so you can get your boss a nice new home on an exotic island. - Way too many characters. I don't know the names of 75% of Red Dead's characters, because they appear like 2 times in the whole game. Not only that, but they are so badly made - they are either very bland and completely lacking any kind of personality or they are so stupidly stereotypical, that their way of acting feels forced as hell. I didn't get emotionally attached to any of them - Every single gun feels absolutely the same. There is literally no reason for you to own more than 1 repeater, they all shoot at the same speed and have similar damage. Even  if they didn't, you're always aiming for the head, right? Why would you even care what damage they have if you always 1-tap your enemy. The revolvers are cool, but  they are useless. The customization options are terrible as well. - Nobody, except for blacks, say 'niÄ¡ger'. When it comes to that word, it's always substituted with 'blackie' or 'darkie'. Now I understand that the slavery is over, but do you REALLY think that after it was abolished and everyone magically started acting like they've always known it was wrong and are totally against it? I don't think so. - Karma system... Are you for real? ... This is a game, where you are the BAD guy, a villain, a robber and a murderer and you put a KARMA system??? I remember RDR1 also having such system, which pissed me off back then as well. So basically - I go to a town, rob a bank, kill 250 police officers and then I go into another town, greet 5 people and my Karma goes up? K. If there was a respect system - that would have been a different story. - Atrocious horse physics. Your horse tips over the tiniest little pebble on the road which can result into it breaking its neck. - Boring missions as a whole. - Dull soundtrack. - The legendary animal clothing is the ugliest abomination in the world. - The inventory management sucks. Too many items doing the exact same thing. Keep these things simple! Why would I need 100 different kinds of food that restore the same stat? - Failed core system. - Glitches, bugs, crashes, launching issues and horrible optimization. - Terrible Ultimate edition items and addons for a stupidly high price. Well, there we go. I'm sorry if you don't agree with me, but that's how I really feel. Everyone has the right to have an opinion and just know that I genuinely feel happy for you, if you are enjoying the game, although I sure as heck didn't! Also.... SOMEBODY ONCE TOLD ME THE WORLD WAS GONNA HANG ME I AIN'T THE SHARPEST OUTLAW AROUND THEY WERE LOOKIN KINDA DUMB WITH THEIR SEMI-AUTO GUNS AND THE PINKERTON BADGE ON THEIR JACKETS WELL WE WON'T STOP RUNNIN AND WE CAN'T STOP RUNNIN BACK TO THE PLAN AND I HIT THE TRAIN GUNNIN DIDN'T MAKE SENSE NOT TO LIVE FOR CASH YOUR PLAN GOES WRONG AND YOUR FRIENDS DIE FAST SO MUCH TO STEAL A GANG TO FEED SO WHAT'S WRONG WITH A BANK ROBBERY IF YOU DOUBT ME YOU'RE NEVER SAFE YOU'LL NEVER MAKE IT IF YOU LOSE FAITH HEY NOW, YOU'RE AN OUTLAW PUT YOUR MASK ON GET PAID HEY NOW, YOU'RE IN MY GANG FOLLOW MY PLAN HAVE FAITH BUT ALL THAT WILD WEST IS GONE ONLY THE ISLANDS HAVE MY MANGOES", "appid": "1174180", "steamid": "profiles/76561198027150734", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1579780800.0}
