{"text": "My personal experience is probably a lot like most people on here. When a sale season hits, you go out a buy a crap-tonne of anything and everything that has had a price reduction on your wishlist. Like a hungry vacuum cleaner sucking up your wallet, purse, handbag, life savings, superannuation and assorted licorices, you just buy buy buy! without really looking at the forums or the latest info or even if the game is finished yet. Which brings me to my point. This game wasn't finished, and never will be. I don't know the finer details but for me, I finished the first 'episode', and thinking I had the whole game purchased, went on to play the next episode, only to get a steam window pop up to the store. The only problem is, while I could add it to my wishlist, I could not buy it. So sayeth the wise shopfront window. The game WOULD have been an enjoyable experience, HAD I been able to finish it. Largely playing out in noir black and white, (with red of course, because seeing copious amounts of blood is Important!) it's a bit of a Sherlock Holmes-esque detective game, with a bit of combat in the form of set-period gunfights, the sort of thing you'd expect from a movie that would feature Al Capone vs a hot-headed cop. The funny thing is I liked the villains better than the main protagonist, I found him a bit of a slow plod. That's not his fault though, that's just the game engine he finds himself in. I mean, I guess 'slow' kind of goes hand-in-hand with 'old person' but the devs could have been a bit more creative with that, no one likes a snooze-fest. If you press the shift button he goes from plodding to shuffling... *exasperated sigh* There's only one deduction board, but it's pretty basic, you just slap photos in slots. If you try to put the wrong photo in a slot you get heart palpitations and everything goes wobbly for a bit so maybe you should lie down and breathe deep, maybe go outside for some fresh air. There was a mutilated body so I don't blame you. ;) There are some other characters but they bored me. I guess the slow pace and LACK OF ANYTHING AFTER EPISODE ONE really got to me. If you've done the same as me and realised you bought a half-finished painting, be sure to get that achievement manager and set the record straight, write a negative review and treat yourself to a tub of your favourite ice cream. The game has been dead for years and their website is down. Down like the Hindenburg.", "appid": "378660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198008683738", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1600689600.0}
