{"text": "Fallout 3 is one of the worst Fallout games and games i've ever played. At first of all I've played another parts like classic fallout or New Vegas or 4 and all these games i like but i don't like f3 cos it's terrible and worse than other games of that series in many aspects.  Everyone knows gameplay is one of more important aspects in every game and everyone has already understood that i'll say gameplay in this game is bad and  they'll be absolutely right. Gameplay is terrible. I don't think anyone likes shooting, yeah VATS helps but anyway i hate that fact when i shoot someone in the head (s)he is still alive and continues shooting me. It's just Oblivion with guns.  The dialogues and quests are another theme. After 83 hrs i didn't notice any interesting or memorable quest and they haven't variability like in classic parts or New Vegas. Even storyline is boring and has a little idiot moments like Little Lamplight or Brotherhood, supermutants and Enclave's presence in the east coast of America... btw what the f8ck Harold is doing there? Also I would like to say one thing about the game lore. Bethesda spoiled it. Forever...  I won't say only bad things about the game. Bethesda made really good and even interesting open world and i was really intrested in exploring it. But anyway i can't recommend this game especially if you've already played NV, 4th or classic parts...  PS yeah 4th part is better and i feel sorry for the time i spent in this crap :d:", "appid": "22300", "steamid": "profiles/76561198862555293", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "20", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1562500800.0}
